82/// Helper types for tracking macro definitions.
83typedef std::vector<AsmToken> MCAsmMacroArgument;
84typedef std::vector<MCAsmMacroArgument> MCAsmMacroArguments;
85
86/// Helper class for storing information about an active macro
87/// instantiation.
88struct MacroInstantiation {
89 /// The location of the instantiation.
90 SMLoc InstantiationLoc;
91
92 /// The buffer where parsing should resume upon instantiation completion.
93 int ExitBuffer;
94
95 /// The location where parsing should resume upon instantiation completion.
96 SMLoc ExitLoc;
97
98 /// The depth of TheCondStack at the start of the instantiation.
99 size_t CondStackDepth;
100
101public:
102 MacroInstantiation(SMLoc IL, int EB, SMLoc EL, size_t CondStackDepth);
103};
104
105struct ParseStatementInfo {
106 /// The parsed operands from the last parsed statement.
107 SmallVector<std::unique_ptr<MCParsedAsmOperand>, 8> ParsedOperands;
108
109 /// The opcode from the last parsed instruction.
110 unsigned Opcode = ~0U;
111
112 /// Was there an error parsing the inline assembly?
113 bool ParseError = false;
114
115 SmallVectorImpl<AsmRewrite> *AsmRewrites = nullptr;
116
117 ParseStatementInfo() = delete;
118 ParseStatementInfo(SmallVectorImpl<AsmRewrite> *rewrites)
119 : AsmRewrites(rewrites) {}
120};

122/// The concrete assembly parser instance.
123class AsmParser : public MCAsmParser {
124private:
125 AsmLexer Lexer;
126 MCContext &Ctx;
127 MCStreamer &Out;
128 const MCAsmInfo &MAI;
129 SourceMgr &SrcMgr;
130 SourceMgr::DiagHandlerTy SavedDiagHandler;
131 void *SavedDiagContext;
132 std::unique_ptr<MCAsmParserExtension> PlatformParser;
133
134 /// This is the current buffer index we're lexing from as managed by the
135 /// SourceMgr object.
136 unsigned CurBuffer;
137
138 AsmCond TheCondState;
139 std::vector<AsmCond> TheCondStack;
140
141 /// maps directive names to handler methods in parser
142 /// extensions. Extensions register themselves in this map by calling
143 /// addDirectiveHandler.
144 StringMap<ExtensionDirectiveHandler> ExtensionDirectiveMap;
145
146 /// Stack of active macro instantiations.
147 std::vector<MacroInstantiation*> ActiveMacros;
148
149 /// List of bodies of anonymous macros.
150 std::deque<MCAsmMacro> MacroLikeBodies;
151
152 /// Boolean tracking whether macro substitution is enabled.
153 unsigned MacrosEnabledFlag : 1;
154
155 /// Keeps track of how many .macro's have been instantiated.
156 unsigned NumOfMacroInstantiations;
157
158 /// The values from the last parsed cpp hash file line comment if any.
159 struct CppHashInfoTy {
160 StringRef Filename;
161 int64_t LineNumber;
162 SMLoc Loc;
163 unsigned Buf;
164 CppHashInfoTy() : Filename(), LineNumber(0), Loc(), Buf(0) {}
165 };
166 CppHashInfoTy CppHashInfo;
167
168 /// The filename from the first cpp hash file line comment, if any.
169 StringRef FirstCppHashFilename;
170
171 /// List of forward directional labels for diagnosis at the end.
172 SmallVector<std::tuple<SMLoc, CppHashInfoTy, MCSymbol *>, 4> DirLabels;
173
174 /// AssemblerDialect. ~OU means unset value and use value provided by MAI.
175 unsigned AssemblerDialect = ~0U;
176
177 /// is Darwin compatibility enabled?
178 bool IsDarwin = false;
179
180 /// Are we parsing ms-style inline assembly?
181 bool ParsingInlineAsm = false;
182
183 /// Did we already inform the user about inconsistent MD5 usage?
184 bool ReportedInconsistentMD5 = false;
185
186 // Is alt macro mode enabled.
187 bool AltMacroMode = false;
188
189public:
190 AsmParser(SourceMgr &SM, MCContext &Ctx, MCStreamer &Out,
191 const MCAsmInfo &MAI, unsigned CB);
192 AsmParser(const AsmParser &) = delete;
193 AsmParser &operator=(const AsmParser &) = delete;
194 ~AsmParser() override;
195
196 bool Run(bool NoInitialTextSection, bool NoFinalize = false) override;
197
198 void addDirectiveHandler(StringRef Directive,
199 ExtensionDirectiveHandler Handler) override {
200 ExtensionDirectiveMap[Directive] = Handler;
201 }
202
203 void addAliasForDirective(StringRef Directive, StringRef Alias) override {
204 DirectiveKindMap[Directive] = DirectiveKindMap[Alias];
205 }
206
207 /// @name MCAsmParser Interface
208 /// {
209
210 SourceMgr &getSourceManager() override { return SrcMgr; }
211 MCAsmLexer &getLexer() override { return Lexer; }
212 MCContext &getContext() override { return Ctx; }
213 MCStreamer &getStreamer() override { return Out; }
214
215 CodeViewContext &getCVContext() { return Ctx.getCVContext(); }
216
217 unsigned getAssemblerDialect() override {
218 if (AssemblerDialect == ~0U)
219 return MAI.getAssemblerDialect();
220 else
221 return AssemblerDialect;
222 }
223 void setAssemblerDialect(unsigned i) override {
224 AssemblerDialect = i;
225 }
226
227 void Note(SMLoc L, const Twine &Msg, SMRange Range = None) override;
228 bool Warning(SMLoc L, const Twine &Msg, SMRange Range = None) override;
229 bool printError(SMLoc L, const Twine &Msg, SMRange Range = None) override;
230
231 const AsmToken &Lex() override;
232
233 void setParsingInlineAsm(bool V) override {
234 ParsingInlineAsm = V;
235 // When parsing MS inline asm, we must lex 0b1101 and 0ABCH as binary and
236 // hex integer literals.
237 Lexer.setLexMasmIntegers(V);
238 }
239 bool isParsingInlineAsm() override { return ParsingInlineAsm; }
240
241 bool parseMSInlineAsm(void *AsmLoc, std::string &AsmString,
242 unsigned &NumOutputs, unsigned &NumInputs,
243 SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<void *,bool>> &OpDecls,
244 SmallVectorImpl<std::string> &Constraints,
245 SmallVectorImpl<std::string> &Clobbers,
246 const MCInstrInfo *MII, const MCInstPrinter *IP,
247 MCAsmParserSemaCallback &SI) override;
248
249 bool parseExpression(const MCExpr *&Res);
250 bool parseExpression(const MCExpr *&Res, SMLoc &EndLoc) override;
251 bool parsePrimaryExpr(const MCExpr *&Res, SMLoc &EndLoc) override;
252 bool parseParenExpression(const MCExpr *&Res, SMLoc &EndLoc) override;
253 bool parseParenExprOfDepth(unsigned ParenDepth, const MCExpr *&Res,
254 SMLoc &EndLoc) override;
255 bool parseAbsoluteExpression(int64_t &Res) override;
256
257 /// Parse a floating point expression using the float \p Semantics
258 /// and set \p Res to the value.
259 bool parseRealValue(const fltSemantics &Semantics, APInt &Res);
260
261 /// Parse an identifier or string (as a quoted identifier)
262 /// and set \p Res to the identifier contents.
263 bool parseIdentifier(StringRef &Res) override;
264 void eatToEndOfStatement() override;
265
266 bool checkForValidSection() override;
267
268 /// }

271 bool parseStatement(ParseStatementInfo &Info,

328 /// Reset the current lexer position to that given by \p Loc. The

333 /// location.
334 void jumpToLoc(SMLoc Loc, unsigned InBuffer = 0);

341 /// Parse until the end of a statement or a comma is encountered,

664 // ".warning"
665 bool parseDirectiveWarning(SMLoc DirectiveLoc);
666
667 // .print <double-quotes-string>
668 bool parseDirectivePrint(SMLoc DirectiveLoc);
669
670 // Directives to support address-significance tables.
671 bool parseDirectiveAddrsig();
672 bool parseDirectiveAddrsigSym();
673
674 // ".chericap"
675 bool parseDirectiveCheriCap(SMLoc DirectiveLoc);
676
677 void initializeDirectiveKindMap();
678};

693AsmParser::AsmParser(SourceMgr &SM, MCContext &Ctx, MCStreamer &Out,
694 const MCAsmInfo &MAI, unsigned CB = 0)
695 : Lexer(MAI), Ctx(Ctx), Out(Out), MAI(MAI), SrcMgr(SM),
696 CurBuffer(CB ? CB : SM.getMainFileID()), MacrosEnabledFlag(true) {
697 HadError = false;
698 // Save the old handler.
699 SavedDiagHandler = SrcMgr.getDiagHandler();
700 SavedDiagContext = SrcMgr.getDiagContext();
701 // Set our own handler which calls the saved handler.
702 SrcMgr.setDiagHandler(DiagHandler, this);
703 Lexer.setBuffer(SrcMgr.getMemoryBuffer(CurBuffer)->getBuffer());
704
705 // Initialize the platform / file format parser.
706 switch (Ctx.getObjectFileInfo()->getObjectFileType()) {
707 case MCObjectFileInfo::IsCOFF:
708 PlatformParser.reset(createCOFFAsmParser());
709 break;
710 case MCObjectFileInfo::IsMachO:
711 PlatformParser.reset(createDarwinAsmParser());
712 IsDarwin = true;
713 break;
714 case MCObjectFileInfo::IsELF:
715 PlatformParser.reset(createELFAsmParser());
716 break;
717 case MCObjectFileInfo::IsWasm:
718 PlatformParser.reset(createWasmAsmParser());
719 break;
720 case MCObjectFileInfo::IsXCOFF:
721 // TODO: Need to implement createXCOFFAsmParser for XCOFF format.
722 break;
723 }
724
725 PlatformParser->Initialize(*this);
726 initializeDirectiveKindMap();
727
728 NumOfMacroInstantiations = 0;
729}

731AsmParser::~AsmParser() {
732 assert((HadError || ActiveMacros.empty()) &&
733 "Unexpected active macro instantiation!");
734
735 // Restore the saved diagnostics handler and context for use during
736 // finalization.
737 SrcMgr.setDiagHandler(SavedDiagHandler, SavedDiagContext);
738}

740void AsmParser::printMacroInstantiations() {
741 // Print the active macro instantiation stack.
742 for (std::vector<MacroInstantiation *>::const_reverse_iterator
743 it = ActiveMacros.rbegin(),
744 ie = ActiveMacros.rend();
745 it != ie; ++it)
746 printMessage((*it)->InstantiationLoc, SourceMgr::DK_Note,
747 "while in macro instantiation");
748}

773bool AsmParser::enterIncludeFile(const std::string &Filename) {
774 std::string IncludedFile;
775 unsigned NewBuf =
776 SrcMgr.AddIncludeFile(Filename, Lexer.getLoc(), IncludedFile);
777 if (!NewBuf)
778 return true;
779
780 CurBuffer = NewBuf;
781 Lexer.setBuffer(SrcMgr.getMemoryBuffer(CurBuffer)->getBuffer());
782 return false;
783}
784
785/// Process the specified .incbin file by searching for it in the include paths
786/// then just emitting the byte contents of the file to the streamer. This
787/// returns true on failure.
788bool AsmParser::processIncbinFile(const std::string &Filename, int64_t Skip,
789 const MCExpr *Count, SMLoc Loc) {
790 std::string IncludedFile;
791 unsigned NewBuf =
792 SrcMgr.AddIncludeFile(Filename, Lexer.getLoc(), IncludedFile);
793 if (!NewBuf)
794 return true;
795
796 // Pick up the bytes from the file and emit them.
797 StringRef Bytes = SrcMgr.getMemoryBuffer(NewBuf)->getBuffer();
798 Bytes = Bytes.drop_front(Skip);
799 if (Count) {
800 int64_t Res;
801 if (!Count->evaluateAsAbsolute(Res, getStreamer().getAssemblerPtr()))
802 return Error(Loc, "expected absolute expression");
803 if (Res < 0)
804 return Warning(Loc, "negative count has no effect");
805 Bytes = Bytes.take_front(Res);
806 }
807 getStreamer().EmitBytes(Bytes);
808 return false;
809}
810
811void AsmParser::jumpToLoc(SMLoc Loc, unsigned InBuffer) {
812 CurBuffer = InBuffer ? InBuffer : SrcMgr.FindBufferContainingLoc(Loc);
813 Lexer.setBuffer(SrcMgr.getMemoryBuffer(CurBuffer)->getBuffer(),
814 Loc.getPointer());
815}
816
817const AsmToken &AsmParser::Lex() {
818 if (Lexer.getTok().is(AsmToken::Error))
819 Error(Lexer.getErrLoc(), Lexer.getErr());
820
821 // if it's a end of statement with a comment in it
822 if (getTok().is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
823 // if this is a line comment output it.
824 if (!getTok().getString().empty() && getTok().getString().front() != '\n' &&
825 getTok().getString().front() != '\r' && MAI.preserveAsmComments())
826 Out.addExplicitComment(Twine(getTok().getString()));
827 }
828
829 const AsmToken *tok = &Lexer.Lex();
830
831 // Parse comments here to be deferred until end of next statement.
832 while (tok->is(AsmToken::Comment)) {
833 if (MAI.preserveAsmComments())
834 Out.addExplicitComment(Twine(tok->getString()));
835 tok = &Lexer.Lex();
836 }
837
838 if (tok->is(AsmToken::Eof)) {
839 // If this is the end of an included file, pop the parent file off the
840 // include stack.
841 SMLoc ParentIncludeLoc = SrcMgr.getParentIncludeLoc(CurBuffer);
842 if (ParentIncludeLoc != SMLoc()) {
843 jumpToLoc(ParentIncludeLoc);
844 return Lex();
845 }
846 }
847
848 return *tok;
849}
850
851bool AsmParser::enabledGenDwarfForAssembly() {
852 // Check whether the user specified -g.
853 if (!getContext().getGenDwarfForAssembly())
854 return false;
855 // If we haven't encountered any .file directives (which would imply that
856 // the assembler source was produced with debug info already) then emit one
857 // describing the assembler source file itself.
858 if (getContext().getGenDwarfFileNumber() == 0) {
859 // Use the first #line directive for this, if any. It's preprocessed, so
860 // there is no checksum, and of course no source directive.
861 if (!FirstCppHashFilename.empty())
862 getContext().setMCLineTableRootFile(/*CUID=*/0,
863 getContext().getCompilationDir(),
864 FirstCppHashFilename,
865 /*Cksum=*/None, /*Source=*/None);
866 const MCDwarfFile &RootFile =
867 getContext().getMCDwarfLineTable(/*CUID=*/0).getRootFile();
868 getContext().setGenDwarfFileNumber(getStreamer().EmitDwarfFileDirective(
869 /*CUID=*/0, getContext().getCompilationDir(), RootFile.Name,
870 RootFile.Checksum, RootFile.Source));
871 }
872 return true;
873}
874
875bool AsmParser::Run(bool NoInitialTextSection, bool NoFinalize) {
876 // Create the initial section, if requested.
877 if (!NoInitialTextSection)
878 Out.InitSections(false);
879
880 // Prime the lexer.
881 Lex();
882
883 HadError = false;
884 AsmCond StartingCondState = TheCondState;
885 SmallVector<AsmRewrite, 4> AsmStrRewrites;
886
887 // If we are generating dwarf for assembly source files save the initial text
888 // section. (Don't use enabledGenDwarfForAssembly() here, as we aren't
889 // emitting any actual debug info yet and haven't had a chance to parse any
890 // embedded .file directives.)
891 if (getContext().getGenDwarfForAssembly()) {
892 MCSection *Sec = getStreamer().getCurrentSectionOnly();
893 if (!Sec->getBeginSymbol()) {
894 MCSymbol *SectionStartSym = getContext().createTempSymbol();
895 getStreamer().EmitLabel(SectionStartSym);
896 Sec->setBeginSymbol(SectionStartSym);
897 }
898 bool InsertResult = getContext().addGenDwarfSection(Sec);
899 assert(InsertResult && ".text section should not have debug info yet");
900 (void)InsertResult;
901 }
902
903 // While we have input, parse each statement.
904 while (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::Eof)) {
905 ParseStatementInfo Info(&AsmStrRewrites);
906 if (!parseStatement(Info, nullptr))
907 continue;
908
909 // If we have a Lexer Error we are on an Error Token. Load in Lexer Error
910 // for printing ErrMsg via Lex() only if no (presumably better) parser error
911 // exists.
912 if (!hasPendingError() && Lexer.getTok().is(AsmToken::Error)) {
913 Lex();
914 }
915
916 // parseStatement returned true so may need to emit an error.
917 printPendingErrors();
918
919 // Skipping to the next line if needed.
920 if (!getLexer().isAtStartOfStatement())
921 eatToEndOfStatement();
922 }
923
924 getTargetParser().onEndOfFile();
925 printPendingErrors();
926
927 // All errors should have been emitted.
928 assert(!hasPendingError() && "unexpected error from parseStatement");
929
930 getTargetParser().flushPendingInstructions(getStreamer());
931
932 if (TheCondState.TheCond != StartingCondState.TheCond ||
933 TheCondState.Ignore != StartingCondState.Ignore)
934 printError(getTok().getLoc(), "unmatched .ifs or .elses");
935 // Check to see there are no empty DwarfFile slots.
936 const auto &LineTables = getContext().getMCDwarfLineTables();
937 if (!LineTables.empty()) {
938 unsigned Index = 0;
939 for (const auto &File : LineTables.begin()->second.getMCDwarfFiles()) {
940 if (File.Name.empty() && Index != 0)
941 printError(getTok().getLoc(), "unassigned file number: " +
942 Twine(Index) +
943 " for .file directives");
944 ++Index;
945 }
946 }
947
948 // Check to see that all assembler local symbols were actually defined.
949 // Targets that don't do subsections via symbols may not want this, though,
950 // so conservatively exclude them. Only do this if we're finalizing, though,
951 // as otherwise we won't necessarilly have seen everything yet.
952 if (!NoFinalize) {
953 if (MAI.hasSubsectionsViaSymbols()) {
954 for (const auto &TableEntry : getContext().getSymbols()) {
955 MCSymbol *Sym = TableEntry.getValue();
956 // Variable symbols may not be marked as defined, so check those
957 // explicitly. If we know it's a variable, we have a definition for
958 // the purposes of this check.
959 if (Sym->isTemporary() && !Sym->isVariable() && !Sym->isDefined())
960 // FIXME: We would really like to refer back to where the symbol was
961 // first referenced for a source location. We need to add something
962 // to track that. Currently, we just point to the end of the file.
963 printError(getTok().getLoc(), "assembler local symbol '" +
964 Sym->getName() + "' not defined");
965 }
966 }
967
968 // Temporary symbols like the ones for directional jumps don't go in the
969 // symbol table. They also need to be diagnosed in all (final) cases.
970 for (std::tuple<SMLoc, CppHashInfoTy, MCSymbol *> &LocSym : DirLabels) {
971 if (std::get<2>(LocSym)->isUndefined()) {
972 // Reset the state of any "# line file" directives we've seen to the
973 // context as it was at the diagnostic site.
974 CppHashInfo = std::get<1>(LocSym);
975 printError(std::get<0>(LocSym), "directional label undefined");
976 }
977 }
978 }
979
980 // Finalize the output stream if there are no errors and if the client wants
981 // us to.
982 if (!HadError && !NoFinalize)
983 Out.Finish();
984
985 return HadError || getContext().hadError();
986}
987
988bool AsmParser::checkForValidSection() {
989 if (!ParsingInlineAsm && !getStreamer().getCurrentSectionOnly()) {
990 Out.InitSections(false);
991 return Error(getTok().getLoc(),
992 "expected section directive before assembly directive");
993 }
994 return false;
995}
996
997/// Throw away the rest of the line for testing purposes.
998void AsmParser::eatToEndOfStatement() {
999 while (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement) && Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::Eof))
1000 Lexer.Lex();
1001
1002 // Eat EOL.
1003 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
1004 Lexer.Lex();
1005}
1006
1007StringRef AsmParser::parseStringToEndOfStatement() {
1008 const char *Start = getTok().getLoc().getPointer();
1009
1010 while (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement) && Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::Eof))
1011 Lexer.Lex();
1012
1013 const char *End = getTok().getLoc().getPointer();
1014 return StringRef(Start, End - Start);
1015}
1016
1017StringRef AsmParser::parseStringToComma() {
1018 const char *Start = getTok().getLoc().getPointer();
1019
1020 while (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement) &&
1021 Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::Comma) && Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::Eof))
1022 Lexer.Lex();
1023
1024 const char *End = getTok().getLoc().getPointer();
1025 return StringRef(Start, End - Start);
1026}

1028/// Parse a paren expression and return it.
1029/// NOTE: This assumes the leading '(' has already been consumed.
1030///
1031/// parenexpr ::= expr)
1032///
1033bool AsmParser::parseParenExpr(const MCExpr *&Res, SMLoc &EndLoc) {
1034 if (parseExpression(Res))
1035 return true;
1036 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::RParen))
1037 return TokError("expected ')' in parentheses expression");
1038 EndLoc = Lexer.getTok().getEndLoc();
1039 Lex();
1040 return false;
1041}
1042
1043/// Parse a bracket expression and return it.
1044/// NOTE: This assumes the leading '[' has already been consumed.
1045///
1046/// bracketexpr ::= expr]
1047///
1048bool AsmParser::parseBracketExpr(const MCExpr *&Res, SMLoc &EndLoc) {
1049 if (parseExpression(Res))
1050 return true;
1051 EndLoc = getTok().getEndLoc();
1052 if (parseToken(AsmToken::RBrac, "expected ']' in brackets expression"))
1053 return true;
1054 return false;
1055}
1056
1057/// Parse a primary expression and return it.
1058/// primaryexpr ::= (parenexpr
1059/// primaryexpr ::= symbol
1060/// primaryexpr ::= number
1061/// primaryexpr ::= '.'
1062/// primaryexpr ::= ~,+,- primaryexpr
1063bool AsmParser::parsePrimaryExpr(const MCExpr *&Res, SMLoc &EndLoc) {
1064 SMLoc FirstTokenLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
1065 AsmToken::TokenKind FirstTokenKind = Lexer.getKind();
1066 switch (FirstTokenKind) {
1067 default:
1068 return TokError("unknown token in expression");
1069 // If we have an error assume that we've already handled it.
1070 case AsmToken::Error:
1071 return true;
1072 case AsmToken::Exclaim:
1073 Lex(); // Eat the operator.
1074 if (parsePrimaryExpr(Res, EndLoc))
1075 return true;
1076 Res = MCUnaryExpr::createLNot(Res, getContext(), FirstTokenLoc);
1077 return false;
1078 case AsmToken::Dollar:
1079 case AsmToken::At:
1080 case AsmToken::String:
1081 case AsmToken::Identifier: {
1082 StringRef Identifier;
1083 if (parseIdentifier(Identifier)) {
1084 // We may have failed but $ may be a valid token.
1085 if (getTok().is(AsmToken::Dollar)) {
1086 if (Lexer.getMAI().getDollarIsPC()) {
1087 Lex();
1088 // This is a '$' reference, which references the current PC. Emit a
1089 // temporary label to the streamer and refer to it.
1090 MCSymbol *Sym = Ctx.createTempSymbol();
1091 Out.EmitLabel(Sym);
1092 Res = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None,
1093 getContext());
1094 EndLoc = FirstTokenLoc;
1095 return false;
1096 }
1097 return Error(FirstTokenLoc, "invalid token in expression");
1098 }
1099 }
1100 // Parse symbol variant
1101 std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> Split;
1102 if (!MAI.useParensForSymbolVariant()) {
1103 if (FirstTokenKind == AsmToken::String) {
1104 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::At)) {
1105 Lex(); // eat @
1106 SMLoc AtLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
1107 StringRef VName;
1108 if (parseIdentifier(VName))
1109 return Error(AtLoc, "expected symbol variant after '@'");
1110
1111 Split = std::make_pair(Identifier, VName);
1112 }
1113 } else {
1114 Split = Identifier.split('@');
1115 }
1116 } else if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::LParen)) {
1117 Lex(); // eat '('.
1118 StringRef VName;
1119 parseIdentifier(VName);
1120 // eat ')'.
1121 if (parseToken(AsmToken::RParen,
1122 "unexpected token in variant, expected ')'"))
1123 return true;
1124 Split = std::make_pair(Identifier, VName);
1125 }
1126
1127 EndLoc = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Identifier.end());
1128
1129 // This is a symbol reference.
1130 StringRef SymbolName = Identifier;
1131 if (SymbolName.empty())
1132 return Error(getLexer().getLoc(), "expected a symbol reference");
1133
1134 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind Variant = MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None;
1135
1136 // Lookup the symbol variant if used.
1137 if (!Split.second.empty()) {
1138 Variant = MCSymbolRefExpr::getVariantKindForName(Split.second);
1139 if (Variant != MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_Invalid) {
1140 SymbolName = Split.first;
1141 } else if (MAI.doesAllowAtInName() && !MAI.useParensForSymbolVariant()) {
1142 Variant = MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None;
1143 } else {
1144 return Error(SMLoc::getFromPointer(Split.second.begin()),
1145 "invalid variant '" + Split.second + "'");
1146 }
1147 }
1148
1149 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(SymbolName);
1150
1151 // If this is an absolute variable reference, substitute it now to preserve
1152 // semantics in the face of reassignment.
1153 if (Sym->isVariable()) {
1154 auto V = Sym->getVariableValue(/*SetUsed*/ false);
1155 bool DoInline = isa<MCConstantExpr>(V) && !Variant;
1156 if (auto TV = dyn_cast<MCTargetExpr>(V))
1157 DoInline = TV->inlineAssignedExpr();
1158 if (DoInline) {
1159 if (Variant)
1160 return Error(EndLoc, "unexpected modifier on variable reference");
1161 Res = Sym->getVariableValue(/*SetUsed*/ false);
1162 return false;
1163 }
1164 }
1165
1166 // Otherwise create a symbol ref.
1167 Res = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, Variant, getContext(), FirstTokenLoc);
1168 return false;
1169 }
1170 case AsmToken::BigNum:
1171 return TokError("literal value out of range for directive");
1172 case AsmToken::Integer: {
1173 SMLoc Loc = getTok().getLoc();
1174 int64_t IntVal = getTok().getIntVal();
1175 Res = MCConstantExpr::create(IntVal, getContext());
1176 EndLoc = Lexer.getTok().getEndLoc();
1177 Lex(); // Eat token.
1178 // Look for 'b' or 'f' following an Integer as a directional label
1179 if (Lexer.getKind() == AsmToken::Identifier) {
1180 StringRef IDVal = getTok().getString();
1181 // Lookup the symbol variant if used.
1182 std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> Split = IDVal.split('@');
1183 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind Variant = MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None;
1184 if (Split.first.size() != IDVal.size()) {
1185 Variant = MCSymbolRefExpr::getVariantKindForName(Split.second);
1186 if (Variant == MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_Invalid)
1187 return TokError("invalid variant '" + Split.second + "'");
1188 IDVal = Split.first;
1189 }
1190 if (IDVal == "f" || IDVal == "b") {
1191 MCSymbol *Sym =
1192 Ctx.getDirectionalLocalSymbol(IntVal, IDVal == "b");
1193 Res = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, Variant, getContext());
1194 if (IDVal == "b" && Sym->isUndefined())
1195 return Error(Loc, "directional label undefined");
1196 DirLabels.push_back(std::make_tuple(Loc, CppHashInfo, Sym));
1197 EndLoc = Lexer.getTok().getEndLoc();
1198 Lex(); // Eat identifier.
1199 }
1200 }
1201 return false;
1202 }
1203 case AsmToken::Real: {
1204 APFloat RealVal(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), getTok().getString());
1205 uint64_t IntVal = RealVal.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue();
1206 Res = MCConstantExpr::create(IntVal, getContext());
1207 EndLoc = Lexer.getTok().getEndLoc();
1208 Lex(); // Eat token.
1209 return false;
1210 }
1211 case AsmToken::Dot: {
1212 // This is a '.' reference, which references the current PC. Emit a
1213 // temporary label to the streamer and refer to it.
1214 MCSymbol *Sym = Ctx.createTempSymbol();
1215 Out.EmitLabel(Sym);
1216 Res = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, getContext());
1217 EndLoc = Lexer.getTok().getEndLoc();
1218 Lex(); // Eat identifier.
1219 return false;
1220 }
1221 case AsmToken::LParen:
1222 Lex(); // Eat the '('.
1223 return parseParenExpr(Res, EndLoc);
1224 case AsmToken::LBrac:
1225 if (!PlatformParser->HasBracketExpressions())
1226 return TokError("brackets expression not supported on this target");
1227 Lex(); // Eat the '['.
1228 return parseBracketExpr(Res, EndLoc);
1229 case AsmToken::Minus:
1230 Lex(); // Eat the operator.
1231 if (parsePrimaryExpr(Res, EndLoc))
1232 return true;
1233 Res = MCUnaryExpr::createMinus(Res, getContext(), FirstTokenLoc);
1234 return false;
1235 case AsmToken::Plus:
1236 Lex(); // Eat the operator.
1237 if (parsePrimaryExpr(Res, EndLoc))
1238 return true;
1239 Res = MCUnaryExpr::createPlus(Res, getContext(), FirstTokenLoc);
1240 return false;
1241 case AsmToken::Tilde:
1242 Lex(); // Eat the operator.
1243 if (parsePrimaryExpr(Res, EndLoc))
1244 return true;
1245 Res = MCUnaryExpr::createNot(Res, getContext(), FirstTokenLoc);
1246 return false;
1247 // MIPS unary expression operators. The lexer won't generate these tokens if
1248 // MCAsmInfo::HasMipsExpressions is false for the target.
1249 case AsmToken::PercentCall16:
1250 case AsmToken::PercentCall_Hi:
1251 case AsmToken::PercentCall_Lo:
1252 case AsmToken::PercentDtprel_Hi:
1253 case AsmToken::PercentDtprel_Lo:
1254 case AsmToken::PercentGot:
1255 case AsmToken::PercentGot_Disp:
1256 case AsmToken::PercentGot_Hi:
1257 case AsmToken::PercentGot_Lo:
1258 case AsmToken::PercentGot_Ofst:
1259 case AsmToken::PercentGot_Page:
1260 case AsmToken::PercentGottprel:
1261 case AsmToken::PercentGp_Rel:
1262 case AsmToken::PercentCapTab_Rel:
1263 case AsmToken::PercentHi:
1264 case AsmToken::PercentHigher:
1265 case AsmToken::PercentHighest:
1266 case AsmToken::PercentLo:
1267 case AsmToken::PercentNeg:
1268 case AsmToken::PercentPcrel_Hi:
1269 case AsmToken::PercentPcrel_Lo:
1270 case AsmToken::PercentTlsgd:
1271 case AsmToken::PercentTlsldm:
1272 case AsmToken::PercentTprel_Hi:
1273 case AsmToken::PercentTprel_Lo:
1274 case AsmToken::PercentCapTab11:
1275 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabCall11:
1276 case AsmToken::PercentCapTab20:
1277 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabCall20:
1278 case AsmToken::PercentCapTab_Lo:
1279 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabCall_Lo:
1280 case AsmToken::PercentCapTab_Hi:
1281 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabCall_Hi:
1282 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabTlsgd_Hi:
1283 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabTlsgd_Lo:
1284 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabTlsldm_Hi:
1285 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabTlsldm_Lo:
1286 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabTprel_Hi:
1287 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabTprel_Lo:
1288 Lex(); // Eat the operator.
1289 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::LParen))
1290 return TokError("expected '(' after operator");
1291 Lex(); // Eat the operator.
1292 if (parseExpression(Res, EndLoc))
1293 return true;
1294 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::RParen))
1295 return TokError("expected ')'");
1296 Lex(); // Eat the operator.
1297 Res = getTargetParser().createTargetUnaryExpr(Res, FirstTokenKind, Ctx);
1298 return !Res;
1299 }
1300}
1301
1302bool AsmParser::parseExpression(const MCExpr *&Res) {
1303 SMLoc EndLoc;
1304 return parseExpression(Res, EndLoc);
1305}
1306
1307const MCExpr *
1308AsmParser::applyModifierToExpr(const MCExpr *E,
1309 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind Variant) {
1310 // Ask the target implementation about this expression first.
1311 const MCExpr *NewE = getTargetParser().applyModifierToExpr(E, Variant, Ctx);
1312 if (NewE)
1313 return NewE;
1314 // Recurse over the given expression, rebuilding it to apply the given variant
1315 // if there is exactly one symbol.
1316 switch (E->getKind()) {
1317 case MCExpr::Target:
1318 case MCExpr::Constant:
1319 return nullptr;
1320
1321 case MCExpr::SymbolRef: {
1322 const MCSymbolRefExpr *SRE = cast<MCSymbolRefExpr>(E);
1323
1324 if (SRE->getKind() != MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None) {
1325 TokError("invalid variant on expression '" + getTok().getIdentifier() +
1326 "' (already modified)");
1327 return E;
1328 }
1329
1330 return MCSymbolRefExpr::create(&SRE->getSymbol(), Variant, getContext());
1331 }
1332
1333 case MCExpr::Unary: {
1334 const MCUnaryExpr *UE = cast<MCUnaryExpr>(E);
1335 const MCExpr *Sub = applyModifierToExpr(UE->getSubExpr(), Variant);
1336 if (!Sub)
1337 return nullptr;
1338 return MCUnaryExpr::create(UE->getOpcode(), Sub, getContext());
1339 }
1340
1341 case MCExpr::Binary: {
1342 const MCBinaryExpr *BE = cast<MCBinaryExpr>(E);
1343 const MCExpr *LHS = applyModifierToExpr(BE->getLHS(), Variant);
1344 const MCExpr *RHS = applyModifierToExpr(BE->getRHS(), Variant);
1345
1346 if (!LHS && !RHS)
1347 return nullptr;
1348
1349 if (!LHS)
1350 LHS = BE->getLHS();
1351 if (!RHS)
1352 RHS = BE->getRHS();
1353
1354 return MCBinaryExpr::create(BE->getOpcode(), LHS, RHS, getContext());
1355 }
1356 }
1357
1358 llvm_unreachable("Invalid expression kind!");
1359}
1360
1361/// This function checks if the next token is <string> type or arithmetic.
1362/// string that begin with character '<' must end with character '>'.
1363/// otherwise it is arithmetics.
1364/// If the function returns a 'true' value,
1365/// the End argument will be filled with the last location pointed to the '>'
1366/// character.
1367
1368/// There is a gap between the AltMacro's documentation and the single quote
1369/// implementation. GCC does not fully support this feature and so we will not
1370/// support it.
1371/// TODO: Adding single quote as a string.
1372static bool isAltmacroString(SMLoc &StrLoc, SMLoc &EndLoc) {
1373 assert((StrLoc.getPointer() != nullptr) &&
1374 "Argument to the function cannot be a NULL value");
1375 const char *CharPtr = StrLoc.getPointer();
1376 while ((*CharPtr != '>') && (*CharPtr != '\n') && (*CharPtr != '\r') &&
1377 (*CharPtr != '\0')) {
1378 if (*CharPtr == '!')
1379 CharPtr++;
1380 CharPtr++;
1381 }
1382 if (*CharPtr == '>') {
1383 EndLoc = StrLoc.getFromPointer(CharPtr + 1);
1384 return true;
1385 }
1386 return false;
1387}
1388
1389/// creating a string without the escape characters '!'.
1390static std::string altMacroString(StringRef AltMacroStr) {
1391 std::string Res;
1392 for (size_t Pos = 0; Pos < AltMacroStr.size(); Pos++) {
1393 if (AltMacroStr[Pos] == '!')
1394 Pos++;
1395 Res += AltMacroStr[Pos];
1396 }
1397 return Res;
1398}
1399
1400/// Parse an expression and return it.
1401///
1402/// expr ::= expr &&,|| expr -> lowest.
1403/// expr ::= expr |,^,&,! expr
1404/// expr ::= expr ==,!=,<>,<,<=,>,>= expr
1405/// expr ::= expr <<,>> expr
1406/// expr ::= expr +,- expr
1407/// expr ::= expr *,/,% expr -> highest.
1408/// expr ::= primaryexpr
1409///
1410bool AsmParser::parseExpression(const MCExpr *&Res, SMLoc &EndLoc) {
1411 // Parse the expression.
1412 Res = nullptr;
1413 if (getTargetParser().parsePrimaryExpr(Res, EndLoc) ||
1414 parseBinOpRHS(1, Res, EndLoc))
1415 return true;
1416
1417 // As a special case, we support 'a op b @ modifier' by rewriting the
1418 // expression to include the modifier. This is inefficient, but in general we
1419 // expect users to use 'a@modifier op b'.
1420 if (Lexer.getKind() == AsmToken::At) {
1421 Lex();
1422
1423 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier))
1424 return TokError("unexpected symbol modifier following '@'");
1425
1426 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind Variant =
1427 MCSymbolRefExpr::getVariantKindForName(getTok().getIdentifier());
1428 if (Variant == MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_Invalid)
1429 return TokError("invalid variant '" + getTok().getIdentifier() + "'");
1430
1431 const MCExpr *ModifiedRes = applyModifierToExpr(Res, Variant);
1432 if (!ModifiedRes) {
1433 return TokError("invalid modifier '" + getTok().getIdentifier() +
1434 "' (no symbols present)");
1435 }
1436
1437 Res = ModifiedRes;
1438 Lex();
1439 }
1440
1441 // Try to constant fold it up front, if possible. Do not exploit
1442 // assembler here.
1443 int64_t Value;
1444 if (Res->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value))
1445 Res = MCConstantExpr::create(Value, getContext());
1446
1447 return false;
1448}
1449
1450bool AsmParser::parseParenExpression(const MCExpr *&Res, SMLoc &EndLoc) {
1451 Res = nullptr;
1452 return parseParenExpr(Res, EndLoc) || parseBinOpRHS(1, Res, EndLoc);
1453}
1454
1455bool AsmParser::parseParenExprOfDepth(unsigned ParenDepth, const MCExpr *&Res,
1456 SMLoc &EndLoc) {
1457 if (parseParenExpr(Res, EndLoc))
1458 return true;
1459
1460 for (; ParenDepth > 0; --ParenDepth) {
1461 if (parseBinOpRHS(1, Res, EndLoc))
1462 return true;
1463
1464 // We don't Lex() the last RParen.
1465 // This is the same behavior as parseParenExpression().
1466 if (ParenDepth - 1 > 0) {
1467 EndLoc = getTok().getEndLoc();
1468 if (parseToken(AsmToken::RParen,
1469 "expected ')' in parentheses expression"))
1470 return true;
1471 }
1472 }
1473 return false;
1474}
1475
1476bool AsmParser::parseAbsoluteExpression(int64_t &Res) {
1477 const MCExpr *Expr;
1478
1479 SMLoc StartLoc = Lexer.getLoc();
1480 if (parseExpression(Expr))
1481 return true;
1482
1483 if (!Expr->evaluateAsAbsolute(Res, getStreamer().getAssemblerPtr()))
1484 return Error(StartLoc, "expected absolute expression");
1485
1486 return false;
1487}
1488
1489static unsigned getDarwinBinOpPrecedence(AsmToken::TokenKind K,
1490 MCBinaryExpr::Opcode &Kind,
1491 bool ShouldUseLogicalShr) {
1492 switch (K) {
1493 default:
1494 return 0; // not a binop.
1495
1496 // Lowest Precedence: &&, ||
1497 case AsmToken::AmpAmp:
1498 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::LAnd;
1499 return 1;
1500 case AsmToken::PipePipe:
1501 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::LOr;
1502 return 1;
1503
1504 // Low Precedence: |, &, ^
1505 //
1506 // FIXME: gas seems to support '!' as an infix operator?
1507 case AsmToken::Pipe:
1508 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::Or;
1509 return 2;
1510 case AsmToken::Caret:
1511 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::Xor;
1512 return 2;
1513 case AsmToken::Amp:
1514 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::And;
1515 return 2;
1516
1517 // Low Intermediate Precedence: ==, !=, <>, <, <=, >, >=
1518 case AsmToken::EqualEqual:
1519 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::EQ;
1520 return 3;
1521 case AsmToken::ExclaimEqual:
1522 case AsmToken::LessGreater:
1523 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::NE;
1524 return 3;
1525 case AsmToken::Less:
1526 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::LT;
1527 return 3;
1528 case AsmToken::LessEqual:
1529 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::LTE;
1530 return 3;
1531 case AsmToken::Greater:
1532 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::GT;
1533 return 3;
1534 case AsmToken::GreaterEqual:
1535 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::GTE;
1536 return 3;
1537
1538 // Intermediate Precedence: <<, >>
1539 case AsmToken::LessLess:
1540 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::Shl;
1541 return 4;
1542 case AsmToken::GreaterGreater:
1543 Kind = ShouldUseLogicalShr ? MCBinaryExpr::LShr : MCBinaryExpr::AShr;
1544 return 4;
1545
1546 // High Intermediate Precedence: +, -
1547 case AsmToken::Plus:
1548 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::Add;
1549 return 5;
1550 case AsmToken::Minus:
1551 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::Sub;
1552 return 5;
1553
1554 // Highest Precedence: *, /, %
1555 case AsmToken::Star:
1556 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::Mul;
1557 return 6;
1558 case AsmToken::Slash:
1559 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::Div;
1560 return 6;
1561 case AsmToken::Percent:
1562 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::Mod;
1563 return 6;
1564 }
1565}

1567static unsigned getGNUBinOpPrecedence(AsmToken::TokenKind K,
1568 MCBinaryExpr::Opcode &Kind,
1569 bool ShouldUseLogicalShr) {
1570 switch (K) {
1571 default:
1572 return 0; // not a binop.
1573
1574 // Lowest Precedence: &&, ||
1575 case AsmToken::AmpAmp:
1576 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::LAnd;
1577 return 2;
1578 case AsmToken::PipePipe:
1579 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::LOr;
1580 return 1;
1581
1582 // Low Precedence: ==, !=, <>, <, <=, >, >=
1583 case AsmToken::EqualEqual:
1584 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::EQ;
1585 return 3;
1586 case AsmToken::ExclaimEqual:
1587 case AsmToken::LessGreater:
1588 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::NE;
1589 return 3;
1590 case AsmToken::Less:
1591 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::LT;
1592 return 3;
1593 case AsmToken::LessEqual:
1594 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::LTE;
1595 return 3;
1596 case AsmToken::Greater:
1597 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::GT;
1598 return 3;
1599 case AsmToken::GreaterEqual:
1600 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::GTE;
1601 return 3;
1602
1603 // Low Intermediate Precedence: +, -
1604 case AsmToken::Plus:
1605 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::Add;
1606 return 4;
1607 case AsmToken::Minus:
1608 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::Sub;
1609 return 4;

1614 case AsmToken::Pipe:
1615 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::Or;
1616 return 5;
1617 case AsmToken::Caret:
1618 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::Xor;
1619 return 5;
1620 case AsmToken::Amp:
1621 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::And;
1622 return 5;
1623
1624 // Highest Precedence: *, /, %, <<, >>
1625 case AsmToken::Star:
1626 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::Mul;
1627 return 6;
1628 case AsmToken::Slash:
1629 Kind = MCBinaryExpr::Div;

1634 case AsmToken::LessLess:

1636 return 6;

1638 Kind = ShouldUseLogicalShr ? MCBinaryExpr::LShr : MCBinaryExpr::AShr;
1639 return 6;
1640 }

1642
1643unsigned AsmParser::getBinOpPrecedence(AsmToken::TokenKind K,
1644 MCBinaryExpr::Opcode &Kind) {
1645 bool ShouldUseLogicalShr = MAI.shouldUseLogicalShr();
1646 return IsDarwin ? getDarwinBinOpPrecedence(K, Kind, ShouldUseLogicalShr)
1647 : getGNUBinOpPrecedence(K, Kind, ShouldUseLogicalShr);
1648}
1649
1650/// Parse all binary operators with precedence >= 'Precedence'.
1651/// Res contains the LHS of the expression on input.
1652bool AsmParser::parseBinOpRHS(unsigned Precedence, const MCExpr *&Res,
1653 SMLoc &EndLoc) {
1654 SMLoc StartLoc = Lexer.getLoc();
1655 while (true) {
1656 MCBinaryExpr::Opcode Kind = MCBinaryExpr::Add;
1657 unsigned TokPrec = getBinOpPrecedence(Lexer.getKind(), Kind);
1658
1659 // If the next token is lower precedence than we are allowed to eat, return
1660 // successfully with what we ate already.
1661 if (TokPrec < Precedence)
1662 return false;
1663
1664 Lex();
1665
1666 // Eat the next primary expression.
1667 const MCExpr *RHS;
1668 if (getTargetParser().parsePrimaryExpr(RHS, EndLoc))
1669 return true;
1670
1671 // If BinOp binds less tightly with RHS than the operator after RHS, let
1672 // the pending operator take RHS as its LHS.
1673 MCBinaryExpr::Opcode Dummy;
1674 unsigned NextTokPrec = getBinOpPrecedence(Lexer.getKind(), Dummy);
1675 if (TokPrec < NextTokPrec && parseBinOpRHS(TokPrec + 1, RHS, EndLoc))
1676 return true;
1677
1678 // Merge LHS and RHS according to operator.
1679 Res = MCBinaryExpr::create(Kind, Res, RHS, getContext(), StartLoc);
1680 }
1681}
1682
1683/// ParseStatement:
1684/// ::= EndOfStatement
1685/// ::= Label* Directive ...Operands... EndOfStatement
1686/// ::= Label* Identifier OperandList* EndOfStatement
1687bool AsmParser::parseStatement(ParseStatementInfo &Info,
1688 MCAsmParserSemaCallback *SI) {
1689 assert(!hasPendingError() && "parseStatement started with pending error");
1690 // Eat initial spaces and comments
1691 while (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Space))
1692 Lex();
1693 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
1694 // if this is a line comment we can drop it safely
1695 if (getTok().getString().empty() || getTok().getString().front() == '\r' ||
1696 getTok().getString().front() == '\n')
1697 Out.AddBlankLine();
1698 Lex();
1699 return false;
1700 }
1701 // Statements always start with an identifier.
1702 AsmToken ID = getTok();
1703 SMLoc IDLoc = ID.getLoc();
1704 StringRef IDVal;
1705 int64_t LocalLabelVal = -1;
1706 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::HashDirective))
1707 return parseCppHashLineFilenameComment(IDLoc);
1708 // Allow an integer followed by a ':' as a directional local label.
1709 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
1710 LocalLabelVal = getTok().getIntVal();
1711 if (LocalLabelVal < 0) {
1712 if (!TheCondState.Ignore) {
1713 Lex(); // always eat a token
1714 return Error(IDLoc, "unexpected token at start of statement");
1715 }
1716 IDVal = "";
1717 } else {
1718 IDVal = getTok().getString();
1719 Lex(); // Consume the integer token to be used as an identifier token.
1720 if (Lexer.getKind() != AsmToken::Colon) {
1721 if (!TheCondState.Ignore) {
1722 Lex(); // always eat a token
1723 return Error(IDLoc, "unexpected token at start of statement");
1724 }
1725 }
1726 }
1727 } else if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Dot)) {
1728 // Treat '.' as a valid identifier in this context.
1729 Lex();
1730 IDVal = ".";
1731 } else if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::LCurly)) {
1732 // Treat '{' as a valid identifier in this context.
1733 Lex();
1734 IDVal = "{";
1735
1736 } else if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::RCurly)) {
1737 // Treat '}' as a valid identifier in this context.
1738 Lex();
1739 IDVal = "}";
1740 } else if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Star) &&
1741 getTargetParser().starIsStartOfStatement()) {
1742 // Accept '*' as a valid start of statement.
1743 Lex();
1744 IDVal = "*";
1745 } else if (parseIdentifier(IDVal)) {
1746 if (!TheCondState.Ignore) {
1747 Lex(); // always eat a token
1748 return Error(IDLoc, "unexpected token at start of statement");
1749 }
1750 IDVal = "";
1751 }
1752
1753 // Handle conditional assembly here before checking for skipping. We
1754 // have to do this so that .endif isn't skipped in a ".if 0" block for
1755 // example.
1756 StringMap<DirectiveKind>::const_iterator DirKindIt =
1757 DirectiveKindMap.find(IDVal);
1758 DirectiveKind DirKind = (DirKindIt == DirectiveKindMap.end())
1759 ? DK_NO_DIRECTIVE
1760 : DirKindIt->getValue();
1761 switch (DirKind) {
1762 default:
1763 break;
1764 case DK_IF:
1765 case DK_IFEQ:
1766 case DK_IFGE:
1767 case DK_IFGT:
1768 case DK_IFLE:
1769 case DK_IFLT:
1770 case DK_IFNE:
1771 return parseDirectiveIf(IDLoc, DirKind);
1772 case DK_IFB:
1773 return parseDirectiveIfb(IDLoc, true);
1774 case DK_IFNB:
1775 return parseDirectiveIfb(IDLoc, false);
1776 case DK_IFC:
1777 return parseDirectiveIfc(IDLoc, true);
1778 case DK_IFEQS:
1779 return parseDirectiveIfeqs(IDLoc, true);
1780 case DK_IFNC:
1781 return parseDirectiveIfc(IDLoc, false);
1782 case DK_IFNES:
1783 return parseDirectiveIfeqs(IDLoc, false);
1784 case DK_IFDEF:
1785 return parseDirectiveIfdef(IDLoc, true);
1786 case DK_IFNDEF:
1787 case DK_IFNOTDEF:
1788 return parseDirectiveIfdef(IDLoc, false);
1789 case DK_ELSEIF:
1790 return parseDirectiveElseIf(IDLoc);
1791 case DK_ELSE:
1792 return parseDirectiveElse(IDLoc);
1793 case DK_ENDIF:
1794 return parseDirectiveEndIf(IDLoc);
1795 }
1796
1797 // Ignore the statement if in the middle of inactive conditional
1798 // (e.g. ".if 0").
1799 if (TheCondState.Ignore) {
1800 eatToEndOfStatement();
1801 return false;
1802 }
1803
1804 // FIXME: Recurse on local labels?
1805
1806 // See what kind of statement we have.
1807 switch (Lexer.getKind()) {
1808 case AsmToken::Colon: {
1809 if (!getTargetParser().isLabel(ID))
1810 break;
1811 if (checkForValidSection())
1812 return true;
1813
1814 // identifier ':' -> Label.
1815 Lex();
1816
1817 // Diagnose attempt to use '.' as a label.
1818 if (IDVal == ".")
1819 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid use of pseudo-symbol '.' as a label");
1820
1821 // Diagnose attempt to use a variable as a label.
1822 //
1823 // FIXME: Diagnostics. Note the location of the definition as a label.
1824 // FIXME: This doesn't diagnose assignment to a symbol which has been
1825 // implicitly marked as external.
1826 MCSymbol *Sym;
1827 if (LocalLabelVal == -1) {
1828 if (ParsingInlineAsm && SI) {
1829 StringRef RewrittenLabel =
1830 SI->LookupInlineAsmLabel(IDVal, getSourceManager(), IDLoc, true);
1831 assert(!RewrittenLabel.empty() &&
1832 "We should have an internal name here.");
1833 Info.AsmRewrites->emplace_back(AOK_Label, IDLoc, IDVal.size(),
1834 RewrittenLabel);
1835 IDVal = RewrittenLabel;
1836 }
1837 Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(IDVal);
1838 } else
1839 Sym = Ctx.createDirectionalLocalSymbol(LocalLabelVal);
1840 // End of Labels should be treated as end of line for lexing
1841 // purposes but that information is not available to the Lexer who
1842 // does not understand Labels. This may cause us to see a Hash
1843 // here instead of a preprocessor line comment.
1844 if (getTok().is(AsmToken::Hash)) {
1845 StringRef CommentStr = parseStringToEndOfStatement();
1846 Lexer.Lex();
1847 Lexer.UnLex(AsmToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement, CommentStr));
1848 }
1849
1850 // Consume any end of statement token, if present, to avoid spurious
1851 // AddBlankLine calls().
1852 if (getTok().is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
1853 Lex();
1854 }
1855
1856 getTargetParser().doBeforeLabelEmit(Sym);
1857
1858 // Emit the label.
1859 if (!getTargetParser().isParsingInlineAsm())
1860 Out.EmitLabel(Sym, IDLoc);
1861
1862 // If we are generating dwarf for assembly source files then gather the
1863 // info to make a dwarf label entry for this label if needed.
1864 if (enabledGenDwarfForAssembly())
1865 MCGenDwarfLabelEntry::Make(Sym, &getStreamer(), getSourceManager(),
1866 IDLoc);
1867
1868 getTargetParser().onLabelParsed(Sym);
1869
1870 return false;
1871 }
1872
1873 case AsmToken::Equal:
1874 if (!getTargetParser().equalIsAsmAssignment())
1875 break;
1876 // identifier '=' ... -> assignment statement
1877 Lex();
1878
1879 return parseAssignment(IDVal, true);
1880
1881 default: // Normal instruction or directive.
1882 break;
1883 }
1884
1885 // If macros are enabled, check to see if this is a macro instantiation.
1886 if (areMacrosEnabled())
1887 if (const MCAsmMacro *M = getContext().lookupMacro(IDVal)) {
1888 return handleMacroEntry(M, IDLoc);
1889 }
1890
1891 // Otherwise, we have a normal instruction or directive.
1892
1893 // Directives start with "."
1894 if (IDVal.startswith(".") && IDVal != ".") {
1895 // There are several entities interested in parsing directives:
1896 //
1897 // 1. The target-specific assembly parser. Some directives are target
1898 // specific or may potentially behave differently on certain targets.
1899 // 2. Asm parser extensions. For example, platform-specific parsers
1900 // (like the ELF parser) register themselves as extensions.
1901 // 3. The generic directive parser implemented by this class. These are
1902 // all the directives that behave in a target and platform independent
1903 // manner, or at least have a default behavior that's shared between
1904 // all targets and platforms.
1905
1906 getTargetParser().flushPendingInstructions(getStreamer());
1907
1908 SMLoc StartTokLoc = getTok().getLoc();
1909 bool TPDirectiveReturn = getTargetParser().ParseDirective(ID);
1910
1911 if (hasPendingError())
1912 return true;
1913 // Currently the return value should be true if we are
1914 // uninterested but as this is at odds with the standard parsing
1915 // convention (return true = error) we have instances of a parsed
1916 // directive that fails returning true as an error. Catch these
1917 // cases as best as possible errors here.
1918 if (TPDirectiveReturn && StartTokLoc != getTok().getLoc())
1919 return true;
1920 // Return if we did some parsing or believe we succeeded.
1921 if (!TPDirectiveReturn || StartTokLoc != getTok().getLoc())
1922 return false;
1923
1924 // Next, check the extension directive map to see if any extension has
1925 // registered itself to parse this directive.
1926 std::pair<MCAsmParserExtension *, DirectiveHandler> Handler =
1927 ExtensionDirectiveMap.lookup(IDVal);
1928 if (Handler.first)
1929 return (*Handler.second)(Handler.first, IDVal, IDLoc);
1930
1931 // Finally, if no one else is interested in this directive, it must be
1932 // generic and familiar to this class.
1933 switch (DirKind) {
1934 default:
1935 break;
1936 case DK_SET:
1937 case DK_EQU:
1938 return parseDirectiveSet(IDVal, true);
1939 case DK_EQUIV:
1940 return parseDirectiveSet(IDVal, false);
1941 case DK_ASCII:
1942 return parseDirectiveAscii(IDVal, false);
1943 case DK_ASCIZ:
1944 case DK_STRING:
1945 return parseDirectiveAscii(IDVal, true);
1946 case DK_BYTE:
1947 case DK_DC_B:
1948 return parseDirectiveValue(IDVal, 1);
1949 case DK_DC:
1950 case DK_DC_W:
1951 case DK_SHORT:
1952 case DK_VALUE:
1953 case DK_2BYTE:
1954 return parseDirectiveValue(IDVal, 2);
1955 case DK_LONG:
1956 case DK_INT:
1957 case DK_4BYTE:
1958 case DK_DC_L:
1959 return parseDirectiveValue(IDVal, 4);
1960 case DK_QUAD:
1961 case DK_8BYTE:
1962 return parseDirectiveValue(IDVal, 8);
1963 case DK_DC_A:
1964 return parseDirectiveValue(
1965 IDVal, getContext().getAsmInfo()->getCodePointerSize());
1966 case DK_OCTA:
1967 return parseDirectiveOctaValue(IDVal);
1968 case DK_SINGLE:
1969 case DK_FLOAT:
1970 case DK_DC_S:
1971 return parseDirectiveRealValue(IDVal, APFloat::IEEEsingle());
1972 case DK_DOUBLE:
1973 case DK_DC_D:
1974 return parseDirectiveRealValue(IDVal, APFloat::IEEEdouble());
1975 case DK_ALIGN: {
1976 bool IsPow2 = !getContext().getAsmInfo()->getAlignmentIsInBytes();
1977 return parseDirectiveAlign(IsPow2, /*ExprSize=*/1);
1978 }
1979 case DK_ALIGN32: {
1980 bool IsPow2 = !getContext().getAsmInfo()->getAlignmentIsInBytes();

2209

2211 Info.AsmRewrites->emplace_back(AOK_EVEN, IDLoc, 4);
2212 if (checkForValidSection())
2213 return true;

2218 bool ParseHadError = getTargetParser().ParseInstruction(IInfo, OpcodeStr, ID,
2219 Info.ParsedOperands);

2227 for (unsigned i = 0; i != Info.ParsedOperands.size(); ++i) {
2228 if (i != 0)
2229 OS << ", ";
2230 Info.ParsedOperands[i]->print(OS);
2231 }
2232 OS << "]";
2233
2234 printMessage(IDLoc, SourceMgr::DK_Note, OS.str());
2235 }

2237 // Fail even if ParseInstruction erroneously returns false.
2238 if (hasPendingError() || ParseHadError)
2239 return true;
2240
2241 // If we are generating dwarf for the current section then generate a .loc
2242 // directive for the instruction.
2243 if (!ParseHadError && enabledGenDwarfForAssembly() &&
2244 getContext().getGenDwarfSectionSyms().count(
2245 getStreamer().getCurrentSectionOnly())) {
2246 unsigned Line;
2247 // XXXAR: CurBuffer is sometimes wrong!!
2248 if (ActiveMacros.empty())
2249 Line = SrcMgr.FindLineNumber(IDLoc/*, CurBuffer */);
2250 else
2251 Line = SrcMgr.FindLineNumber(ActiveMacros.front()->InstantiationLoc,
2252 ActiveMacros.front()->ExitBuffer);
2253
2254 // If we previously parsed a cpp hash file line comment then make sure the
2255 // current Dwarf File is for the CppHashFilename if not then emit the
2256 // Dwarf File table for it and adjust the line number for the .loc.
2257 if (!CppHashInfo.Filename.empty()) {
2258 unsigned FileNumber = getStreamer().EmitDwarfFileDirective(
2259 0, StringRef(), CppHashInfo.Filename);
2260 getContext().setGenDwarfFileNumber(FileNumber);
2261
2262 unsigned CppHashLocLineNo =
2263 SrcMgr.FindLineNumber(CppHashInfo.Loc, CppHashInfo.Buf);
2264 Line = CppHashInfo.LineNumber - 1 + (Line - CppHashLocLineNo);
2265 }
2266
2267 getStreamer().EmitDwarfLocDirective(
2268 getContext().getGenDwarfFileNumber(), Line, 0,
2269 DWARF2_LINE_DEFAULT_IS_STMT ? DWARF2_FLAG_IS_STMT : 0, 0, 0,
2270 StringRef());
2271 }
2272
2273 // If parsing succeeded, match the instruction.
2274 if (!ParseHadError) {
2275 uint64_t ErrorInfo;
2276 if (getTargetParser().MatchAndEmitInstruction(
2277 IDLoc, Info.Opcode, Info.ParsedOperands, Out, ErrorInfo,
2278 getTargetParser().isParsingInlineAsm()))
2279 return true;
2280 }
2281 return false;
2282}

2284// Parse and erase curly braces marking block start/end
2285bool
2286AsmParser::parseCurlyBlockScope(SmallVectorImpl<AsmRewrite> &AsmStrRewrites) {
2287 // Identify curly brace marking block start/end
2288 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::LCurly) && Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::RCurly))
2289 return false;
2290
2291 SMLoc StartLoc = Lexer.getLoc();
2292 Lex(); // Eat the brace
2293 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
2294 Lex(); // Eat EndOfStatement following the brace
2295
2296 // Erase the block start/end brace from the output asm string
2297 AsmStrRewrites.emplace_back(AOK_Skip, StartLoc, Lexer.getLoc().getPointer() -
2298 StartLoc.getPointer());
2299 return true;
2300}

2302/// parseCppHashLineFilenameComment as this:
2303/// ::= # number "filename"
2304bool AsmParser::parseCppHashLineFilenameComment(SMLoc L) {
2305 Lex(); // Eat the hash token.
2306 // Lexer only ever emits HashDirective if it fully formed if it's
2307 // done the checking already so this is an internal error.
2308 assert(getTok().is(AsmToken::Integer) &&
2309 "Lexing Cpp line comment: Expected Integer");
2310 int64_t LineNumber = getTok().getIntVal();
2311 Lex();
2312 assert(getTok().is(AsmToken::String) &&
2313 "Lexing Cpp line comment: Expected String");
2314 StringRef Filename = getTok().getString();
2315 Lex();
2316
2317 // Get rid of the enclosing quotes.
2318 Filename = Filename.substr(1, Filename.size() - 2);
2319
2320 // Save the SMLoc, Filename and LineNumber for later use by diagnostics
2321 // and possibly DWARF file info.
2322 CppHashInfo.Loc = L;
2323 CppHashInfo.Filename = Filename;
2324 CppHashInfo.LineNumber = LineNumber;
2325 CppHashInfo.Buf = CurBuffer;
2326 if (FirstCppHashFilename.empty())
2327 FirstCppHashFilename = Filename;
2328 return false;
2329}

2331/// will use the last parsed cpp hash line filename comment
2332/// for the Filename and LineNo if any in the diagnostic.
2333void AsmParser::DiagHandler(const SMDiagnostic &Diag, void *Context) {
2334 const AsmParser *Parser = static_cast<const AsmParser *>(Context);
2335 raw_ostream &OS = errs();
2336
2337 const SourceMgr &DiagSrcMgr = *Diag.getSourceMgr();
2338 SMLoc DiagLoc = Diag.getLoc();
2339 unsigned DiagBuf = DiagSrcMgr.FindBufferContainingLoc(DiagLoc);
2340 unsigned CppHashBuf =
2341 Parser->SrcMgr.FindBufferContainingLoc(Parser->CppHashInfo.Loc);
2342
2343 // Like SourceMgr::printMessage() we need to print the include stack if any
2344 // before printing the message.
2345 unsigned DiagCurBuffer = DiagSrcMgr.FindBufferContainingLoc(DiagLoc);
2346 if (!Parser->SavedDiagHandler && DiagCurBuffer &&
2347 DiagCurBuffer != DiagSrcMgr.getMainFileID()) {
2348 SMLoc ParentIncludeLoc = DiagSrcMgr.getParentIncludeLoc(DiagCurBuffer);
2349 DiagSrcMgr.PrintIncludeStack(ParentIncludeLoc, OS);
2350 }
2351
2352 // If we have not parsed a cpp hash line filename comment or the source
2353 // manager changed or buffer changed (like in a nested include) then just
2354 // print the normal diagnostic using its Filename and LineNo.
2355 if (!Parser->CppHashInfo.LineNumber || &DiagSrcMgr != &Parser->SrcMgr ||
2356 DiagBuf != CppHashBuf) {
2357 if (Parser->SavedDiagHandler)
2358 Parser->SavedDiagHandler(Diag, Parser->SavedDiagContext);
2359 else
2360 Diag.print(nullptr, OS);
2361 return;
2362 }
2363
2364 // Use the CppHashFilename and calculate a line number based on the
2365 // CppHashInfo.Loc and CppHashInfo.LineNumber relative to this Diag's SMLoc
2366 // for the diagnostic.
2367 const std::string &Filename = Parser->CppHashInfo.Filename;
2368
2369 int DiagLocLineNo = DiagSrcMgr.FindLineNumber(DiagLoc, DiagBuf);
2370 int CppHashLocLineNo =
2371 Parser->SrcMgr.FindLineNumber(Parser->CppHashInfo.Loc, CppHashBuf);
2372 int LineNo =
2373 Parser->CppHashInfo.LineNumber - 1 + (DiagLocLineNo - CppHashLocLineNo);
2374
2375 SMDiagnostic NewDiag(*Diag.getSourceMgr(), Diag.getLoc(), Filename, LineNo,
2376 Diag.getColumnNo(), Diag.getKind(), Diag.getMessage(),
2377 Diag.getLineContents(), Diag.getRanges());
2378
2379 if (Parser->SavedDiagHandler)
2380 Parser->SavedDiagHandler(NewDiag, Parser->SavedDiagContext);
2381 else
2382 NewDiag.print(nullptr, OS);
2383}

2385// FIXME: This is mostly duplicated from the function in AsmLexer.cpp. The
2386// difference being that that function accepts '@' as part of identifiers and
2387// we can't do that. AsmLexer.cpp should probably be changed to handle
2388// '@' as a special case when needed.
2389static bool isIdentifierChar(char c) {
2390 return isalnum(static_cast<unsigned char>(c)) || c == '_' || c == '$' ||
2391 c == '.';
2392}
2393
2394bool AsmParser::expandMacro(raw_svector_ostream &OS, StringRef Body,
2395 ArrayRef<MCAsmMacroParameter> Parameters,
2396 ArrayRef<MCAsmMacroArgument> A,
2397 bool EnableAtPseudoVariable, SMLoc L) {
2398 unsigned NParameters = Parameters.size();
2399 bool HasVararg = NParameters ? Parameters.back().Vararg : false;
2400 if ((!IsDarwin || NParameters != 0) && NParameters != A.size())
2401 return Error(L, "Wrong number of arguments");
2402
2403 // A macro without parameters is handled differently on Darwin:
2404 // gas accepts no arguments and does no substitutions
2405 while (!Body.empty()) {
2406 // Scan for the next substitution.
2407 std::size_t End = Body.size(), Pos = 0;
2408 for (; Pos != End; ++Pos) {
2409 // Check for a substitution or escape.
2410 if (IsDarwin && !NParameters) {
2411 // This macro has no parameters, look for $0, $1, etc.
2412 if (Body[Pos] != '$' || Pos + 1 == End)
2413 continue;
2414
2415 char Next = Body[Pos + 1];
2416 if (Next == '$' || Next == 'n' ||
2417 isdigit(static_cast<unsigned char>(Next)))
2418 break;
2419 } else {
2420 // This macro has parameters, look for \foo, \bar, etc.
2421 if (Body[Pos] == '\\' && Pos + 1 != End)
2422 break;
2423 }
2424 }
2425
2426 // Add the prefix.
2427 OS << Body.slice(0, Pos);
2428
2429 // Check if we reached the end.
2430 if (Pos == End)
2431 break;
2432
2433 if (IsDarwin && !NParameters) {
2434 switch (Body[Pos + 1]) {
2435 // $$ => $
2436 case '$':
2437 OS << '$';
2438 break;
2439
2440 // $n => number of arguments
2441 case 'n':
2442 OS << A.size();
2443 break;
2444
2445 // $[0-9] => argument
2446 default: {
2447 // Missing arguments are ignored.
2448 unsigned Index = Body[Pos + 1] - '0';
2449 if (Index >= A.size())
2450 break;
2451
2452 // Otherwise substitute with the token values, with spaces eliminated.
2453 for (const AsmToken &Token : A[Index])
2454 OS << Token.getString();
2455 break;
2456 }
2457 }
2458 Pos += 2;
2459 } else {
2460 unsigned I = Pos + 1;
2461
2462 // Check for the \@ pseudo-variable.
2463 if (EnableAtPseudoVariable && Body[I] == '@' && I + 1 != End)
2464 ++I;
2465 else
2466 while (isIdentifierChar(Body[I]) && I + 1 != End)
2467 ++I;
2468
2469 const char *Begin = Body.data() + Pos + 1;
2470 StringRef Argument(Begin, I - (Pos + 1));
2471 unsigned Index = 0;
2472
2473 if (Argument == "@") {
2474 OS << NumOfMacroInstantiations;
2475 Pos += 2;
2476 } else {
2477 for (; Index < NParameters; ++Index)
2478 if (Parameters[Index].Name == Argument)
2479 break;
2480
2481 if (Index == NParameters) {
2482 if (Body[Pos + 1] == '(' && Body[Pos + 2] == ')')
2483 Pos += 3;
2484 else {
2485 OS << '\\' << Argument;
2486 Pos = I;
2487 }
2488 } else {
2489 bool VarargParameter = HasVararg && Index == (NParameters - 1);
2490 for (const AsmToken &Token : A[Index])
2491 // For altmacro mode, you can write '%expr'.
2492 // The prefix '%' evaluates the expression 'expr'
2493 // and uses the result as a string (e.g. replace %(1+2) with the
2494 // string "3").
2495 // Here, we identify the integer token which is the result of the
2496 // absolute expression evaluation and replace it with its string
2497 // representation.
2498 if (AltMacroMode && Token.getString().front() == '%' &&
2499 Token.is(AsmToken::Integer))
2500 // Emit an integer value to the buffer.
2501 OS << Token.getIntVal();
2502 // Only Token that was validated as a string and begins with '<'
2503 // is considered altMacroString!!!
2504 else if (AltMacroMode && Token.getString().front() == '<' &&
2505 Token.is(AsmToken::String)) {
2506 OS << altMacroString(Token.getStringContents());
2507 }
2508 // We expect no quotes around the string's contents when
2509 // parsing for varargs.
2510 else if (Token.isNot(AsmToken::String) || VarargParameter)
2511 OS << Token.getString();
2512 else
2513 OS << Token.getStringContents();
2514
2515 Pos += 1 + Argument.size();
2516 }
2517 }
2518 }
2519 // Update the scan point.
2520 Body = Body.substr(Pos);
2521 }
2522
2523 return false;
2524}

2578
2579bool AsmParser::parseMacroArgument(MCAsmMacroArgument &MA, bool Vararg) {
2580
2581 if (Vararg) {
2582 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
2583 StringRef Str = parseStringToEndOfStatement();
2584 MA.emplace_back(AsmToken::String, Str);
2585 }
2586 return false;
2587 }
2588
2589 unsigned ParenLevel = 0;
2590
2591 // Darwin doesn't use spaces to delmit arguments.
2592 AsmLexerSkipSpaceRAII ScopedSkipSpace(Lexer, IsDarwin);
2593
2594 bool SpaceEaten;
2595
2596 while (true) {
2597 SpaceEaten = false;
2598 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Eof) || Lexer.is(AsmToken::Equal))
2599 return TokError("unexpected token in macro instantiation");
2600
2601 if (ParenLevel == 0) {
2602
2603 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Comma))
2604 break;
2605
2606 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Space)) {
2607 SpaceEaten = true;
2608 Lexer.Lex(); // Eat spaces
2609 }
2610
2611 // Spaces can delimit parameters, but could also be part an expression.
2612 // If the token after a space is an operator, add the token and the next
2613 // one into this argument
2614 if (!IsDarwin) {
2615 if (isOperator(Lexer.getKind())) {
2616 MA.push_back(getTok());
2617 Lexer.Lex();
2618
2619 // Whitespace after an operator can be ignored.
2620 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Space))
2621 Lexer.Lex();
2622
2623 continue;
2624 }
2625 }
2626 if (SpaceEaten)
2627 break;
2628 }
2629
2630 // handleMacroEntry relies on not advancing the lexer here
2631 // to be able to fill in the remaining default parameter values
2632 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
2633 break;
2634
2635 // Adjust the current parentheses level.
2636 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::LParen))
2637 ++ParenLevel;
2638 else if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::RParen) && ParenLevel)
2639 --ParenLevel;
2640
2641 // Append the token to the current argument list.
2642 MA.push_back(getTok());
2643 Lexer.Lex();
2644 }
2645
2646 if (ParenLevel != 0)
2647 return TokError("unbalanced parentheses in macro argument");
2648 return false;
2649}
2650
2651// Parse the macro instantiation arguments.
2652bool AsmParser::parseMacroArguments(const MCAsmMacro *M,
2653 MCAsmMacroArguments &A) {
2654 const unsigned NParameters = M ? M->Parameters.size() : 0;
2655 bool NamedParametersFound = false;
2656 SmallVector<SMLoc, 4> FALocs;
2657
2658 A.resize(NParameters);
2659 FALocs.resize(NParameters);
2660
2661 // Parse two kinds of macro invocations:
2662 // - macros defined without any parameters accept an arbitrary number of them
2663 // - macros defined with parameters accept at most that many of them
2664 bool HasVararg = NParameters ? M->Parameters.back().Vararg : false;
2665 for (unsigned Parameter = 0; !NParameters || Parameter < NParameters;
2666 ++Parameter) {
2667 SMLoc IDLoc = Lexer.getLoc();
2668 MCAsmMacroParameter FA;
2669
2670 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Identifier) && Lexer.peekTok().is(AsmToken::Equal)) {
2671 if (parseIdentifier(FA.Name))
2672 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid argument identifier for formal argument");
2673
2674 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::Equal))
2675 return TokError("expected '=' after formal parameter identifier");
2676
2677 Lex();
2678
2679 NamedParametersFound = true;
2680 }
2681 bool Vararg = HasVararg && Parameter == (NParameters - 1);
2682
2683 if (NamedParametersFound && FA.Name.empty())
2684 return Error(IDLoc, "cannot mix positional and keyword arguments");
2685
2686 SMLoc StrLoc = Lexer.getLoc();
2687 SMLoc EndLoc;
2688 if (AltMacroMode && Lexer.is(AsmToken::Percent)) {
2689 const MCExpr *AbsoluteExp;
2690 int64_t Value;
2691 /// Eat '%'
2692 Lex();
2693 if (parseExpression(AbsoluteExp, EndLoc))
2694 return false;
2695 if (!AbsoluteExp->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value,
2696 getStreamer().getAssemblerPtr()))
2697 return Error(StrLoc, "expected absolute expression");
2698 const char *StrChar = StrLoc.getPointer();
2699 const char *EndChar = EndLoc.getPointer();
2700 AsmToken newToken(AsmToken::Integer,
2701 StringRef(StrChar, EndChar - StrChar), Value);
2702 FA.Value.push_back(newToken);
2703 } else if (AltMacroMode && Lexer.is(AsmToken::Less) &&
2704 isAltmacroString(StrLoc, EndLoc)) {
2705 const char *StrChar = StrLoc.getPointer();
2706 const char *EndChar = EndLoc.getPointer();
2707 jumpToLoc(EndLoc, CurBuffer);
2708 /// Eat from '<' to '>'
2709 Lex();
2710 AsmToken newToken(AsmToken::String,
2711 StringRef(StrChar, EndChar - StrChar));
2712 FA.Value.push_back(newToken);
2713 } else if(parseMacroArgument(FA.Value, Vararg))
2714 return true;
2715
2716 unsigned PI = Parameter;
2717 if (!FA.Name.empty()) {
2718 unsigned FAI = 0;
2719 for (FAI = 0; FAI < NParameters; ++FAI)
2720 if (M->Parameters[FAI].Name == FA.Name)
2721 break;
2722
2723 if (FAI >= NParameters) {
2724 assert(M && "expected macro to be defined");
2725 return Error(IDLoc, "parameter named '" + FA.Name +
2726 "' does not exist for macro '" + M->Name + "'");
2727 }
2728 PI = FAI;
2729 }
2730
2731 if (!FA.Value.empty()) {
2732 if (A.size() <= PI)
2733 A.resize(PI + 1);
2734 A[PI] = FA.Value;
2735
2736 if (FALocs.size() <= PI)
2737 FALocs.resize(PI + 1);
2738
2739 FALocs[PI] = Lexer.getLoc();
2740 }
2741
2742 // At the end of the statement, fill in remaining arguments that have
2743 // default values. If there aren't any, then the next argument is
2744 // required but missing
2745 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
2746 bool Failure = false;
2747 for (unsigned FAI = 0; FAI < NParameters; ++FAI) {
2748 if (A[FAI].empty()) {
2749 if (M->Parameters[FAI].Required) {
2750 Error(FALocs[FAI].isValid() ? FALocs[FAI] : Lexer.getLoc(),
2751 "missing value for required parameter "
2752 "'" + M->Parameters[FAI].Name + "' in macro '" + M->Name + "'");
2753 Failure = true;
2754 }
2755
2756 if (!M->Parameters[FAI].Value.empty())
2757 A[FAI] = M->Parameters[FAI].Value;
2758 }
2759 }
2760 return Failure;
2761 }
2762
2763 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Comma))
2764 Lex();
2765 }
2766
2767 return TokError("too many positional arguments");
2768}
2769
2770bool AsmParser::handleMacroEntry(const MCAsmMacro *M, SMLoc NameLoc) {
2771 // Arbitrarily limit macro nesting depth (default matches 'as'). We can
2772 // eliminate this, although we should protect against infinite loops.
2773 unsigned MaxNestingDepth = AsmMacroMaxNestingDepth;
2774 if (ActiveMacros.size() == MaxNestingDepth) {
2775 std::ostringstream MaxNestingDepthError;
2776 MaxNestingDepthError << "macros cannot be nested more than "
2777 << MaxNestingDepth << " levels deep."
2778 << " Use -asm-macro-max-nesting-depth to increase "
2779 "this limit.";
2780 return TokError(MaxNestingDepthError.str());
2781 }
2782
2783 MCAsmMacroArguments A;
2784 if (parseMacroArguments(M, A))
2785 return true;
2786
2787 // Macro instantiation is lexical, unfortunately. We construct a new buffer
2788 // to hold the macro body with substitutions.
2789 SmallString<256> Buf;
2790 StringRef Body = M->Body;
2791 raw_svector_ostream OS(Buf);
2792
2793 if (expandMacro(OS, Body, M->Parameters, A, true, getTok().getLoc()))
2794 return true;
2795
2796 // We include the .endmacro in the buffer as our cue to exit the macro
2797 // instantiation.
2798 OS << ".endmacro\n";
2799
2800 std::unique_ptr<MemoryBuffer> Instantiation =
2801 MemoryBuffer::getMemBufferCopy(OS.str(), "<instantiation>");
2802
2803 // Create the macro instantiation object and add to the current macro
2804 // instantiation stack.
2805 MacroInstantiation *MI = new MacroInstantiation(
2806 NameLoc, CurBuffer, getTok().getLoc(), TheCondStack.size());
2807 ActiveMacros.push_back(MI);
2808
2809 ++NumOfMacroInstantiations;
2810
2811 // Jump to the macro instantiation and prime the lexer.
2812 CurBuffer = SrcMgr.AddNewSourceBuffer(std::move(Instantiation), SMLoc());
2813 Lexer.setBuffer(SrcMgr.getMemoryBuffer(CurBuffer)->getBuffer());
2814 Lex();
2815
2816 return false;
2817}
2818
2819void AsmParser::handleMacroExit() {
2820 // Jump to the EndOfStatement we should return to, and consume it.
2821 jumpToLoc(ActiveMacros.back()->ExitLoc, ActiveMacros.back()->ExitBuffer);
2822 Lex();
2823
2824 // Pop the instantiation entry.
2825 delete ActiveMacros.back();
2826 ActiveMacros.pop_back();
2827}

2829bool AsmParser::parseAssignment(StringRef Name, bool allow_redef,
2830 bool NoDeadStrip) {
2831 MCSymbol *Sym;
2832 const MCExpr *Value;
2833 if (MCParserUtils::parseAssignmentExpression(Name, allow_redef, *this, Sym,
2834 Value))
2835 return true;
2836
2837 if (!Sym) {
2838 // In the case where we parse an expression starting with a '.', we will
2839 // not generate an error, nor will we create a symbol. In this case we
2840 // should just return out.
2841 return false;
2842 }
2843
2844 // Do the assignment.
2845 Out.EmitAssignment(Sym, Value);
2846 if (NoDeadStrip)
2847 Out.EmitSymbolAttribute(Sym, MCSA_NoDeadStrip);
2848
2849 return false;
2850}
2851
2852/// parseIdentifier:
2853/// ::= identifier
2854/// ::= string
2855bool AsmParser::parseIdentifier(StringRef &Res) {
2856 // The assembler has relaxed rules for accepting identifiers, in particular we
2857 // allow things like '.globl $foo' and '.def @feat.00', which would normally be
2858 // separate tokens. At this level, we have already lexed so we cannot (currently)
2859 // handle this as a context dependent token, instead we detect adjacent tokens
2860 // and return the combined identifier.
2861 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Dollar) || Lexer.is(AsmToken::At)) {
2862 SMLoc PrefixLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
2863
2864 // Consume the prefix character, and check for a following identifier.
2865
2866 AsmToken Buf[1];
2867 Lexer.peekTokens(Buf, false);
2868
2869 if (Buf[0].isNot(AsmToken::Identifier))
2870 return true;
2871
2872 // We have a '$' or '@' followed by an identifier, make sure they are adjacent.
2873 if (PrefixLoc.getPointer() + 1 != Buf[0].getLoc().getPointer())
2874 return true;
2875
2876 // eat $ or @
2877 Lexer.Lex(); // Lexer's Lex guarantees consecutive token.
2878 // Construct the joined identifier and consume the token.
2879 Res =
2880 StringRef(PrefixLoc.getPointer(), getTok().getIdentifier().size() + 1);
2881 Lex(); // Parser Lex to maintain invariants.
2882 return false;
2883 }
2884
2885 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier) && Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::String))
2886 return true;
2887
2888 Res = getTok().getIdentifier();
2889
2890 Lex(); // Consume the identifier token.
2891
2892 return false;
2893}

2895/// parseDirectiveSet:
2896/// ::= .equ identifier ',' expression
2897/// ::= .equiv identifier ',' expression
2898/// ::= .set identifier ',' expression
2899bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveSet(StringRef IDVal, bool allow_redef) {
2900 StringRef Name;
2901 if (check(parseIdentifier(Name), "expected identifier") ||
2902 parseToken(AsmToken::Comma) || parseAssignment(Name, allow_redef, true))
2903 return addErrorSuffix(" in '" + Twine(IDVal) + "' directive");
2904 return false;
2905}
2906
2907bool AsmParser::parseEscapedString(std::string &Data) {
2908 if (check(getTok().isNot(AsmToken::String), "expected string"))
2909 return true;
2910
2911 Data = "";
2912 StringRef Str = getTok().getStringContents();
2913 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Str.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2914 if (Str[i] != '\\') {
2915 Data += Str[i];
2916 continue;
2917 }
2918
2919 // Recognize escaped characters. Note that this escape semantics currently
2920 // loosely follows Darwin 'as'. Notably, it doesn't support hex escapes.
2921 ++i;
2922 if (i == e)
2923 return TokError("unexpected backslash at end of string");
2924
2925 // Recognize octal sequences.
2926 if ((unsigned)(Str[i] - '0') <= 7) {
2927 // Consume up to three octal characters.
2928 unsigned Value = Str[i] - '0';
2929
2930 if (i + 1 != e && ((unsigned)(Str[i + 1] - '0')) <= 7) {
2931 ++i;
2932 Value = Value * 8 + (Str[i] - '0');
2933
2934 if (i + 1 != e && ((unsigned)(Str[i + 1] - '0')) <= 7) {
2935 ++i;
2936 Value = Value * 8 + (Str[i] - '0');
2937 }
2938 }
2939
2940 if (Value > 255)
2941 return TokError("invalid octal escape sequence (out of range)");
2942
2943 Data += (unsigned char)Value;
2944 continue;
2945 }
2946
2947 // Otherwise recognize individual escapes.
2948 switch (Str[i]) {
2949 default:
2950 // Just reject invalid escape sequences for now.
2951 return TokError("invalid escape sequence (unrecognized character)");
2952
2953 case 'b': Data += '\b'; break;
2954 case 'f': Data += '\f'; break;
2955 case 'n': Data += '\n'; break;
2956 case 'r': Data += '\r'; break;
2957 case 't': Data += '\t'; break;
2958 case '"': Data += '"'; break;
2959 case '\\': Data += '\\'; break;
2960 }
2961 }
2962
2963 Lex();
2964 return false;
2965}

2967/// parseDirectiveAscii:
2968/// ::= ( .ascii | .asciz | .string ) [ "string" ( , "string" )* ]
2969bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveAscii(StringRef IDVal, bool ZeroTerminated) {
2970 auto parseOp = [&]() -> bool {
2971 std::string Data;
2972 if (checkForValidSection() || parseEscapedString(Data))
2973 return true;
2974 getStreamer().EmitBytes(Data);
2975 if (ZeroTerminated)
2976 getStreamer().EmitBytes(StringRef("\0", 1));
2977 return false;
2978 };
2979
2980 if (parseMany(parseOp))
2981 return addErrorSuffix(" in '" + Twine(IDVal) + "' directive");
2982 return false;
2983}

2985/// parseDirectiveReloc
2986/// ::= .reloc expression , identifier [ , expression ]
2987bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveReloc(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
2988 const MCExpr *Offset;
2989 const MCExpr *Expr = nullptr;
2990 int64_t OffsetValue;
2991 SMLoc OffsetLoc = Lexer.getTok().getLoc();
2992
2993 if (parseExpression(Offset))
2994 return true;
2995
2996 if ((Offset->evaluateAsAbsolute(OffsetValue,
2997 getStreamer().getAssemblerPtr()) &&
2998 check(OffsetValue < 0, OffsetLoc, "expression is negative")) ||
2999 (check(Offset->getKind() != llvm::MCExpr::Constant &&
3000 Offset->getKind() != llvm::MCExpr::SymbolRef,
3001 OffsetLoc, "expected non-negative number or a label")) ||
3002 (parseToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected comma") ||
3003 check(getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier), "expected relocation name")))
3004 return true;
3005
3006 SMLoc NameLoc = Lexer.getTok().getLoc();
3007 StringRef Name = Lexer.getTok().getIdentifier();
3008 Lex();
3009
3010 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Comma)) {
3011 Lex();
3012 SMLoc ExprLoc = Lexer.getLoc();
3013 if (parseExpression(Expr))
3014 return true;
3015
3016 MCValue Value;
3017 if (!Expr->evaluateAsRelocatable(Value, nullptr, nullptr))
3018 return Error(ExprLoc, "expression must be relocatable");
3019 }
3020
3021 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
3022 "unexpected token in .reloc directive"))
3023 return true;
3024
3025 const MCTargetAsmParser &MCT = getTargetParser();
3026 const MCSubtargetInfo &STI = MCT.getSTI();
3027 if (getStreamer().EmitRelocDirective(*Offset, Name, Expr, DirectiveLoc, STI))
3028 return Error(NameLoc, "unknown relocation name");
3029
3030 return false;
3031}

3033/// parseDirectiveValue
3034/// ::= (.byte | .short | ... ) [ expression (, expression)* ]
3035bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveValue(StringRef IDVal, unsigned Size) {
3036 auto parseOp = [&]() -> bool {
3037 const MCExpr *Value;
3038 SMLoc ExprLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
3039 if (checkForValidSection() || parseExpression(Value))
3040 return true;
3041 // Special case constant expressions to match code generator.
3042 if (const MCConstantExpr *MCE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Value)) {
3043 assert(Size <= 8 && "Invalid size");
3044 uint64_t IntValue = MCE->getValue();
3045 if (!isUIntN(8 * Size, IntValue) && !isIntN(8 * Size, IntValue))
3046 return Error(ExprLoc, "out of range literal value");
3047 getStreamer().EmitIntValue(IntValue, Size);
3048 } else
3049 getStreamer().EmitValue(Value, Size, ExprLoc);
3050 return false;
3051 };
3052
3053 if (parseMany(parseOp))
3054 return addErrorSuffix(" in '" + Twine(IDVal) + "' directive");
3055 return false;
3056}

3058static bool parseHexOcta(AsmParser &Asm, uint64_t &hi, uint64_t &lo) {
3059 if (Asm.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Integer) &&
3060 Asm.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::BigNum))
3061 return Asm.TokError("unknown token in expression");
3062 SMLoc ExprLoc = Asm.getTok().getLoc();
3063 APInt IntValue = Asm.getTok().getAPIntVal();
3064 Asm.Lex();
3065 if (!IntValue.isIntN(128))
3066 return Asm.Error(ExprLoc, "out of range literal value");
3067 if (!IntValue.isIntN(64)) {
3068 hi = IntValue.getHiBits(IntValue.getBitWidth() - 64).getZExtValue();
3069 lo = IntValue.getLoBits(64).getZExtValue();
3070 } else {
3071 hi = 0;
3072 lo = IntValue.getZExtValue();
3073 }
3074 return false;
3075}

3077/// ParseDirectiveOctaValue
3078/// ::= .octa [ hexconstant (, hexconstant)* ]
3079
3080bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveOctaValue(StringRef IDVal) {

3083 return true;

3086 return true;
3087 if (MAI.isLittleEndian()) {
3088 getStreamer().EmitIntValue(lo, 8);
3089 getStreamer().EmitIntValue(hi, 8);
3090 } else {
3091 getStreamer().EmitIntValue(hi, 8);
3092 getStreamer().EmitIntValue(lo, 8);

3094 return false;

3099 return false;

3102bool AsmParser::parseRealValue(const fltSemantics &Semantics, APInt &Res) {
3103 // We don't truly support arithmetic on floating point expressions, so we
3104 // have to manually parse unary prefixes.
3105 bool IsNeg = false;
3106 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Minus)) {
3107 Lexer.Lex();
3108 IsNeg = true;
3109 } else if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Plus))
3110 Lexer.Lex();
3111
3112 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Error))
3113 return TokError(Lexer.getErr());
3114 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::Integer) && Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::Real) &&
3115 Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier))
3116 return TokError("unexpected token in directive");
3117
3118 // Convert to an APFloat.
3119 APFloat Value(Semantics);
3120 StringRef IDVal = getTok().getString();
3121 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
3122 if (!IDVal.compare_lower("infinity") || !IDVal.compare_lower("inf"))
3123 Value = APFloat::getInf(Semantics);
3124 else if (!IDVal.compare_lower("nan"))
3125 Value = APFloat::getNaN(Semantics, false, ~0);
3126 else
3127 return TokError("invalid floating point literal");
3128 } else if (Value.convertFromString(IDVal, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven) ==
3129 APFloat::opInvalidOp)
3130 return TokError("invalid floating point literal");
3131 if (IsNeg)
3132 Value.changeSign();
3133
3134 // Consume the numeric token.
3135 Lex();
3136
3137 Res = Value.bitcastToAPInt();
3138
3139 return false;
3140}

3157 return false;

3161/// ::= .zero expression
3162bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveZero() {

3165 if (checkForValidSection() || parseExpression(NumBytes))
3166 return true;
