3183/// parseDirectiveFill
3184/// ::= .fill expression [ , expression [ , expression ] ]
3185bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveFill() {
3186 SMLoc NumValuesLoc = Lexer.getLoc();
3187 const MCExpr *NumValues;
3188 if (checkForValidSection() || parseExpression(NumValues))
3189 return true;
3190
3191 int64_t FillSize = 1;
3192 int64_t FillExpr = 0;
3193
3194 SMLoc SizeLoc, ExprLoc;
3195
3196 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma)) {
3197 SizeLoc = getTok().getLoc();
3198 if (parseAbsoluteExpression(FillSize))
3199 return true;
3200 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma)) {
3201 ExprLoc = getTok().getLoc();
3202 if (parseAbsoluteExpression(FillExpr))
3203 return true;
3204 }
3205 }
3206 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
3207 "unexpected token in '.fill' directive"))
3208 return true;
3209
3210 if (FillSize < 0) {
3211 Warning(SizeLoc, "'.fill' directive with negative size has no effect");
3212 return false;
3213 }
3214 if (FillSize > 8) {
3215 Warning(SizeLoc, "'.fill' directive with size greater than 8 has been truncated to 8");
3216 FillSize = 8;
3217 }
3218
3219 if (!isUInt<32>(FillExpr) && FillSize > 4)
3220 Warning(ExprLoc, "'.fill' directive pattern has been truncated to 32-bits");
3221
3222 getStreamer().emitFill(*NumValues, FillSize, FillExpr, NumValuesLoc);
3223
3224 return false;
3225}

3246
3247/// parseDirectiveAlign
3248/// ::= {.align, ...} expression [ , expression [ , expression ]]
3249bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveAlign(bool IsPow2, unsigned ValueSize) {
3250 SMLoc AlignmentLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
3251 int64_t Alignment;
3252 SMLoc MaxBytesLoc;
3253 bool HasFillExpr = false;
3254 int64_t FillExpr = 0;
3255 int64_t MaxBytesToFill = 0;
3256
3257 auto parseAlign = [&]() -> bool {
3258 if (parseAbsoluteExpression(Alignment))
3259 return true;
3260 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma)) {
3261 // The fill expression can be omitted while specifying a maximum number of
3262 // alignment bytes, e.g:
3263 // .align 3,,4
3264 if (getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Comma)) {
3265 HasFillExpr = true;
3266 if (parseAbsoluteExpression(FillExpr))
3267 return true;
3268 }
3269 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma))
3270 if (parseTokenLoc(MaxBytesLoc) ||
3271 parseAbsoluteExpression(MaxBytesToFill))
3272 return true;
3273 }
3274 return parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement);
3275 };
3276
3277 if (checkForValidSection())
3278 return addErrorSuffix(" in directive");
3279 // Ignore empty '.p2align' directives for GNU-as compatibility
3280 if (IsPow2 && (ValueSize == 1) && getTok().is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
3281 Warning(AlignmentLoc, "p2align directive with no operand(s) is ignored");
3282 return parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement);
3283 }
3284 if (parseAlign())
3285 return addErrorSuffix(" in directive");
3286
3287 // Always emit an alignment here even if we thrown an error.
3288 bool ReturnVal = false;
3289
3290 // Compute alignment in bytes.
3291 if (IsPow2) {
3292 // FIXME: Diagnose overflow.
3293 if (Alignment >= 32) {
3294 ReturnVal |= Error(AlignmentLoc, "invalid alignment value");
3295 Alignment = 31;
3296 }
3297
3298 Alignment = 1ULL << Alignment;
3299 } else {
3300 // Reject alignments that aren't either a power of two or zero,
3301 // for gas compatibility. Alignment of zero is silently rounded
3302 // up to one.
3303 if (Alignment == 0)
3304 Alignment = 1;
3305 if (!isPowerOf2_64(Alignment))
3306 ReturnVal |= Error(AlignmentLoc, "alignment must be a power of 2");
3307 }
3308
3309 // Diagnose non-sensical max bytes to align.
3310 if (MaxBytesLoc.isValid()) {
3311 if (MaxBytesToFill < 1) {
3312 ReturnVal |= Error(MaxBytesLoc,
3313 "alignment directive can never be satisfied in this "
3314 "many bytes, ignoring maximum bytes expression");
3315 MaxBytesToFill = 0;
3316 }
3317
3318 if (MaxBytesToFill >= Alignment) {
3319 Warning(MaxBytesLoc, "maximum bytes expression exceeds alignment and "
3320 "has no effect");
3321 MaxBytesToFill = 0;
3322 }
3323 }
3324
3325 // Check whether we should use optimal code alignment for this .align
3326 // directive.
3327 const MCSection *Section = getStreamer().getCurrentSectionOnly();
3328 assert(Section && "must have section to emit alignment");
3329 bool UseCodeAlign = Section->UseCodeAlign();
3330 if ((!HasFillExpr || Lexer.getMAI().getTextAlignFillValue() == FillExpr) &&
3331 ValueSize == 1 && UseCodeAlign) {
3332 getStreamer().EmitCodeAlignment(Alignment, MaxBytesToFill);
3333 } else {
3334 // FIXME: Target specific behavior about how the "extra" bytes are filled.
3335 getStreamer().EmitValueToAlignment(Alignment, FillExpr, ValueSize,
3336 MaxBytesToFill);
3337 }
3338
3339 return ReturnVal;
3340}
3341
3342/// parseDirectiveFile
3343/// ::= .file filename
3344/// ::= .file number [directory] filename [md5 checksum] [source source-text]
3345bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveFile(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
3346 // FIXME: I'm not sure what this is.
3347 int64_t FileNumber = -1;
3348 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
3349 FileNumber = getTok().getIntVal();
3350 Lex();
3351
3352 if (FileNumber < 0)
3353 return TokError("negative file number");
3354 }
3355
3356 std::string Path;
3357
3358 // Usually the directory and filename together, otherwise just the directory.
3359 // Allow the strings to have escaped octal character sequence.
3360 if (check(getTok().isNot(AsmToken::String),
3361 "unexpected token in '.file' directive") ||
3362 parseEscapedString(Path))
3363 return true;
3364
3365 StringRef Directory;
3366 StringRef Filename;
3367 std::string FilenameData;
3368 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::String)) {
3369 if (check(FileNumber == -1,
3370 "explicit path specified, but no file number") ||
3371 parseEscapedString(FilenameData))
3372 return true;
3373 Filename = FilenameData;
3374 Directory = Path;
3375 } else {
3376 Filename = Path;
3377 }
3378
3379 uint64_t MD5Hi, MD5Lo;
3380 bool HasMD5 = false;
3381
3382 Optional<StringRef> Source;
3383 bool HasSource = false;
3384 std::string SourceString;
3385
3386 while (!parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
3387 StringRef Keyword;
3388 if (check(getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier),
3389 "unexpected token in '.file' directive") ||
3390 parseIdentifier(Keyword))
3391 return true;
3392 if (Keyword == "md5") {
3393 HasMD5 = true;
3394 if (check(FileNumber == -1,
3395 "MD5 checksum specified, but no file number") ||
3396 parseHexOcta(*this, MD5Hi, MD5Lo))
3397 return true;
3398 } else if (Keyword == "source") {
3399 HasSource = true;
3400 if (check(FileNumber == -1,
3401 "source specified, but no file number") ||
3402 check(getTok().isNot(AsmToken::String),
3403 "unexpected token in '.file' directive") ||
3404 parseEscapedString(SourceString))
3405 return true;
3406 } else {
3407 return TokError("unexpected token in '.file' directive");
3408 }
3409 }
3410
3411 if (FileNumber == -1) {
3412 // Ignore the directive if there is no number and the target doesn't support
3413 // numberless .file directives. This allows some portability of assembler
3414 // between different object file formats.
3415 if (getContext().getAsmInfo()->hasSingleParameterDotFile())
3416 getStreamer().EmitFileDirective(Filename);
3417 } else {
3418 // In case there is a -g option as well as debug info from directive .file,
3419 // we turn off the -g option, directly use the existing debug info instead.
3420 // Also reset any implicit ".file 0" for the assembler source.
3421 if (Ctx.getGenDwarfForAssembly()) {
3422 Ctx.getMCDwarfLineTable(0).resetRootFile();
3423 Ctx.setGenDwarfForAssembly(false);
3424 }
3425
3426 Optional<MD5::MD5Result> CKMem;
3427 if (HasMD5) {
3428 MD5::MD5Result Sum;
3429 for (unsigned i = 0; i != 8; ++i) {
3430 Sum.Bytes[i] = uint8_t(MD5Hi >> ((7 - i) * 8));
3431 Sum.Bytes[i + 8] = uint8_t(MD5Lo >> ((7 - i) * 8));
3432 }
3433 CKMem = Sum;
3434 }
3435 if (HasSource) {
3436 char *SourceBuf = static_cast<char *>(Ctx.allocate(SourceString.size()));
3437 memcpy(SourceBuf, SourceString.data(), SourceString.size());
3438 Source = StringRef(SourceBuf, SourceString.size());
3439 }
3440 if (FileNumber == 0) {
3441 if (Ctx.getDwarfVersion() < 5)
3442 return Warning(DirectiveLoc, "file 0 not supported prior to DWARF-5");
3443 getStreamer().emitDwarfFile0Directive(Directory, Filename, CKMem, Source);
3444 } else {
3445 Expected<unsigned> FileNumOrErr = getStreamer().tryEmitDwarfFileDirective(
3446 FileNumber, Directory, Filename, CKMem, Source);
3447 if (!FileNumOrErr)
3448 return Error(DirectiveLoc, toString(FileNumOrErr.takeError()));
3449 FileNumber = FileNumOrErr.get();
3450 }
3451 // Alert the user if there are some .file directives with MD5 and some not.
3452 // But only do that once.
3453 if (!ReportedInconsistentMD5 && !Ctx.isDwarfMD5UsageConsistent(0)) {
3454 ReportedInconsistentMD5 = true;
3455 return Warning(DirectiveLoc, "inconsistent use of MD5 checksums");
3456 }
3457 }
3458
3459 return false;
3460}

3465 int64_t LineNumber;
3466 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
3467 if (parseIntToken(LineNumber, "unexpected token in '.line' directive"))
3468 return true;
3469 (void)LineNumber;
3470 // FIXME: Do something with the .line.

3479/// parseDirectiveLoc
3480/// ::= .loc FileNumber [LineNumber] [ColumnPos] [basic_block] [prologue_end]
3481/// [epilogue_begin] [is_stmt VALUE] [isa VALUE]
3482/// The first number is a file number, must have been previously assigned with
3483/// a .file directive, the second number is the line number and optionally the
3484/// third number is a column position (zero if not specified). The remaining
3485/// optional items are .loc sub-directives.
3486bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveLoc() {
3487 int64_t FileNumber = 0, LineNumber = 0;
3488 SMLoc Loc = getTok().getLoc();
3489 if (parseIntToken(FileNumber, "unexpected token in '.loc' directive") ||
3490 check(FileNumber < 1 && Ctx.getDwarfVersion() < 5, Loc,
3491 "file number less than one in '.loc' directive") ||
3492 check(!getContext().isValidDwarfFileNumber(FileNumber), Loc,
3493 "unassigned file number in '.loc' directive"))
3494 return true;
3495
3496 // optional
3497 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
3498 LineNumber = getTok().getIntVal();
3499 if (LineNumber < 0)
3500 return TokError("line number less than zero in '.loc' directive");
3501 Lex();
3502 }
3503
3504 int64_t ColumnPos = 0;
3505 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
3506 ColumnPos = getTok().getIntVal();
3507 if (ColumnPos < 0)
3508 return TokError("column position less than zero in '.loc' directive");
3509 Lex();
3510 }
3511
3512 unsigned Flags = DWARF2_LINE_DEFAULT_IS_STMT ? DWARF2_FLAG_IS_STMT : 0;
3513 unsigned Isa = 0;
3514 int64_t Discriminator = 0;
3515
3516 auto parseLocOp = [&]() -> bool {
3517 StringRef Name;
3518 SMLoc Loc = getTok().getLoc();
3519 if (parseIdentifier(Name))
3520 return TokError("unexpected token in '.loc' directive");
3521
3522 if (Name == "basic_block")
3523 Flags |= DWARF2_FLAG_BASIC_BLOCK;
3524 else if (Name == "prologue_end")
3525 Flags |= DWARF2_FLAG_PROLOGUE_END;
3526 else if (Name == "epilogue_begin")
3527 Flags |= DWARF2_FLAG_EPILOGUE_BEGIN;
3528 else if (Name == "is_stmt") {
3529 Loc = getTok().getLoc();
3530 const MCExpr *Value;
3531 if (parseExpression(Value))
3532 return true;
3533 // The expression must be the constant 0 or 1.
3534 if (const MCConstantExpr *MCE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Value)) {
3535 int Value = MCE->getValue();
3536 if (Value == 0)
3537 Flags &= ~DWARF2_FLAG_IS_STMT;
3538 else if (Value == 1)
3539 Flags |= DWARF2_FLAG_IS_STMT;
3540 else
3541 return Error(Loc, "is_stmt value not 0 or 1");
3542 } else {
3543 return Error(Loc, "is_stmt value not the constant value of 0 or 1");
3544 }
3545 } else if (Name == "isa") {
3546 Loc = getTok().getLoc();
3547 const MCExpr *Value;
3548 if (parseExpression(Value))
3549 return true;
3550 // The expression must be a constant greater or equal to 0.
3551 if (const MCConstantExpr *MCE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Value)) {
3552 int Value = MCE->getValue();
3553 if (Value < 0)
3554 return Error(Loc, "isa number less than zero");
3555 Isa = Value;
3556 } else {
3557 return Error(Loc, "isa number not a constant value");
3558 }
3559 } else if (Name == "discriminator") {
3560 if (parseAbsoluteExpression(Discriminator))
3561 return true;
3562 } else {
3563 return Error(Loc, "unknown sub-directive in '.loc' directive");
3564 }
3565 return false;
3566 };
3567
3568 if (parseMany(parseLocOp, false /*hasComma*/))
3569 return true;
3570
3571 getStreamer().EmitDwarfLocDirective(FileNumber, LineNumber, ColumnPos, Flags,
3572 Isa, Discriminator, StringRef());
3573
3574 return false;
3575}

3583/// parseDirectiveCVFile
3584/// ::= .cv_file number filename [checksum] [checksumkind]
3585bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveCVFile() {
3586 SMLoc FileNumberLoc = getTok().getLoc();
3587 int64_t FileNumber;
3588 std::string Filename;
3589 std::string Checksum;
3590 int64_t ChecksumKind = 0;
3591
3592 if (parseIntToken(FileNumber,
3593 "expected file number in '.cv_file' directive") ||
3594 check(FileNumber < 1, FileNumberLoc, "file number less than one") ||
3595 check(getTok().isNot(AsmToken::String),
3596 "unexpected token in '.cv_file' directive") ||
3597 parseEscapedString(Filename))
3598 return true;
3599 if (!parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
3600 if (check(getTok().isNot(AsmToken::String),
3601 "unexpected token in '.cv_file' directive") ||
3602 parseEscapedString(Checksum) ||
3603 parseIntToken(ChecksumKind,
3604 "expected checksum kind in '.cv_file' directive") ||
3605 parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
3606 "unexpected token in '.cv_file' directive"))
3607 return true;
3608 }
3609
3610 Checksum = fromHex(Checksum);
3611 void *CKMem = Ctx.allocate(Checksum.size(), 1);
3612 memcpy(CKMem, Checksum.data(), Checksum.size());
3613 ArrayRef<uint8_t> ChecksumAsBytes(reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(CKMem),
3614 Checksum.size());
3615
3616 if (!getStreamer().EmitCVFileDirective(FileNumber, Filename, ChecksumAsBytes,
3617 static_cast<uint8_t>(ChecksumKind)))
3618 return Error(FileNumberLoc, "file number already allocated");
3619
3620 return false;
3621}

3663/// parseDirectiveCVInlineSiteId
3664/// ::= .cv_inline_site_id FunctionId
3665/// "within" IAFunc
3666/// "inlined_at" IAFile IALine [IACol]
3667///

3669/// at" source location information for use in the line table of the caller,

3671bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveCVInlineSiteId() {

3674 int64_t IAFunc;
3675 int64_t IAFile;
3676 int64_t IALine;
3677 int64_t IACol = 0;
3678
3679 // FunctionId
3680 if (parseCVFunctionId(FunctionId, ".cv_inline_site_id"))
3681 return true;
3682

3692 return true;
3693

3699 return true;
3700 Lex();

3705 return true;
3706
3707 // [IACol]
3708 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
3709 IACol = getTok().getIntVal();
3710 Lex();
3711 }
3712
3713 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
3714 "unexpected token in '.cv_inline_site_id' directive"))
3715 return true;
3716
3717 if (!getStreamer().EmitCVInlineSiteIdDirective(FunctionId, IAFunc, IAFile,
3718 IALine, IACol, FunctionIdLoc))
3719 return Error(FunctionIdLoc, "function id already allocated");
3720

3724/// parseDirectiveCVLoc
3725/// ::= .cv_loc FunctionId FileNumber [LineNumber] [ColumnPos] [prologue_end]
3726/// [is_stmt VALUE]
3727/// The first number is a file number, must have been previously assigned with
3728/// a .file directive, the second number is the line number and optionally the
3729/// third number is a column position (zero if not specified). The remaining
3730/// optional items are .loc sub-directives.
3731bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveCVLoc() {
3732 SMLoc DirectiveLoc = getTok().getLoc();
3733 int64_t FunctionId, FileNumber;
3734 if (parseCVFunctionId(FunctionId, ".cv_loc") ||
3735 parseCVFileId(FileNumber, ".cv_loc"))
3736 return true;
3737
3738 int64_t LineNumber = 0;
3739 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
3740 LineNumber = getTok().getIntVal();
3741 if (LineNumber < 0)
3742 return TokError("line number less than zero in '.cv_loc' directive");
3743 Lex();
3744 }
3745
3746 int64_t ColumnPos = 0;
3747 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
3748 ColumnPos = getTok().getIntVal();
3749 if (ColumnPos < 0)
3750 return TokError("column position less than zero in '.cv_loc' directive");
3751 Lex();
3752 }
3753
3754 bool PrologueEnd = false;
3755 uint64_t IsStmt = 0;
3756
3757 auto parseOp = [&]() -> bool {
3758 StringRef Name;
3759 SMLoc Loc = getTok().getLoc();
3760 if (parseIdentifier(Name))
3761 return TokError("unexpected token in '.cv_loc' directive");
3762 if (Name == "prologue_end")
3763 PrologueEnd = true;
3764 else if (Name == "is_stmt") {
3765 Loc = getTok().getLoc();
3766 const MCExpr *Value;
3767 if (parseExpression(Value))
3768 return true;
3769 // The expression must be the constant 0 or 1.
3770 IsStmt = ~0ULL;
3771 if (const auto *MCE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Value))
3772 IsStmt = MCE->getValue();
3773
3774 if (IsStmt > 1)
3775 return Error(Loc, "is_stmt value not 0 or 1");
3776 } else {
3777 return Error(Loc, "unknown sub-directive in '.cv_loc' directive");
3778 }
3779 return false;
3780 };
3781
3782 if (parseMany(parseOp, false /*hasComma*/))
3783 return true;
3784
3785 getStreamer().EmitCVLocDirective(FunctionId, FileNumber, LineNumber,
3786 ColumnPos, PrologueEnd, IsStmt, StringRef(),
3787 DirectiveLoc);
3788 return false;
3789}

3909/// parseDirectiveCVFileChecksumOffset
3910/// ::= .cv_filechecksumoffset fileno

4106static bool isValidEncoding(int64_t Encoding) {
4107 if (Encoding & ~0xff)
4108 return false;
4109
4110 if (Encoding == dwarf::DW_EH_PE_omit)
4111 return true;
4112
4113 const unsigned Format = Encoding & 0xf;
4114 if (Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_absptr && Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_udata2 &&
4115 Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_udata4 && Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_udata8 &&
4116 Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_sdata2 && Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_sdata4 &&
4117 Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_sdata8 && Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_signed)
4118 return false;
4119
4120 const unsigned Application = Encoding & 0x70;
4121 if (Application != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_absptr &&
4122 Application != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_pcrel)
4123 return false;
4124
4125 return true;
4126}

4130/// ::= .cfi_personality encoding, [symbol_name]
4131/// ::= .cfi_lsda encoding, [symbol_name]
4132bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveCFIPersonalityOrLsda(bool IsPersonality) {

4275/// parseDirectiveMacro
4276/// ::= .macro name[,] [parameters]
4277bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveMacro(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
4278 StringRef Name;
4279 if (parseIdentifier(Name))
4280 return TokError("expected identifier in '.macro' directive");
4281
4282 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Comma))
4283 Lex();
4284
4285 MCAsmMacroParameters Parameters;
4286 while (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
4287
4288 if (!Parameters.empty() && Parameters.back().Vararg)
4289 return Error(Lexer.getLoc(),
4290 "Vararg parameter '" + Parameters.back().Name +
4291 "' should be last one in the list of parameters.");
4292
4293 MCAsmMacroParameter Parameter;
4294 if (parseIdentifier(Parameter.Name))
4295 return TokError("expected identifier in '.macro' directive");
4296
4297 // Emit an error if two (or more) named parameters share the same name
4298 for (const MCAsmMacroParameter& CurrParam : Parameters)
4299 if (CurrParam.Name.equals(Parameter.Name))
4300 return TokError("macro '" + Name + "' has multiple parameters"
4301 " named '" + Parameter.Name + "'");
4302
4303 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Colon)) {
4304 Lex(); // consume ':'
4305
4306 SMLoc QualLoc;
4307 StringRef Qualifier;
4308
4309 QualLoc = Lexer.getLoc();
4310 if (parseIdentifier(Qualifier))
4311 return Error(QualLoc, "missing parameter qualifier for "
4312 "'" + Parameter.Name + "' in macro '" + Name + "'");
4313
4314 if (Qualifier == "req")
4315 Parameter.Required = true;
4316 else if (Qualifier == "vararg")
4317 Parameter.Vararg = true;
4318 else
4319 return Error(QualLoc, Qualifier + " is not a valid parameter qualifier "
4320 "for '" + Parameter.Name + "' in macro '" + Name + "'");
4321 }
4322
4323 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Equal)) {
4324 Lex();
4325
4326 SMLoc ParamLoc;
4327
4328 ParamLoc = Lexer.getLoc();
4329 if (parseMacroArgument(Parameter.Value, /*Vararg=*/false ))
4330 return true;
4331
4332 if (Parameter.Required)
4333 Warning(ParamLoc, "pointless default value for required parameter "
4334 "'" + Parameter.Name + "' in macro '" + Name + "'");
4335 }
4336
4337 Parameters.push_back(std::move(Parameter));
4338
4339 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Comma))
4340 Lex();
4341 }
4342
4343 // Eat just the end of statement.
4344 Lexer.Lex();
4345
4346 // Consuming deferred text, so use Lexer.Lex to ignore Lexing Errors
4347 AsmToken EndToken, StartToken = getTok();
4348 unsigned MacroDepth = 0;
4349 // Lex the macro definition.
4350 while (true) {
4351 // Ignore Lexing errors in macros.
4352 while (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Error)) {
4353 Lexer.Lex();
4354 }
4355
4356 // Check whether we have reached the end of the file.
4357 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Eof))
4358 return Error(DirectiveLoc, "no matching '.endmacro' in definition");
4359
4360 // Otherwise, check whether we have reach the .endmacro.
4361 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
4362 if (getTok().getIdentifier() == ".endm" ||
4363 getTok().getIdentifier() == ".endmacro") {
4364 if (MacroDepth == 0) { // Outermost macro.
4365 EndToken = getTok();
4366 Lexer.Lex();
4367 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
4368 return TokError("unexpected token in '" + EndToken.getIdentifier() +
4369 "' directive");
4370 break;
4371 } else {
4372 // Otherwise we just found the end of an inner macro.
4373 --MacroDepth;
4374 }
4375 } else if (getTok().getIdentifier() == ".macro") {
4376 // We allow nested macros. Those aren't instantiated until the outermost
4377 // macro is expanded so just ignore them for now.
4378 ++MacroDepth;
4379 }
4380 }
4381
4382 // Otherwise, scan til the end of the statement.
4383 eatToEndOfStatement();
4384 }
4385
4386 if (getContext().lookupMacro(Name)) {
4387 return Error(DirectiveLoc, "macro '" + Name + "' is already defined");
4388 }
4389
4390 const char *BodyStart = StartToken.getLoc().getPointer();
4391 const char *BodyEnd = EndToken.getLoc().getPointer();
4392 StringRef Body = StringRef(BodyStart, BodyEnd - BodyStart);
4393 checkForBadMacro(DirectiveLoc, Name, Body, Parameters);
4394 MCAsmMacro Macro(Name, Body, std::move(Parameters));
4395 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-macros", dbgs() << "Defining new macro:\n";
4396 Macro.dump());
4397 getContext().defineMacro(Name, std::move(Macro));
4398 return false;
4399}
4400
4401/// checkForBadMacro
4402///
4403/// With the support added for named parameters there may be code out there that
4404/// is transitioning from positional parameters. In versions of gas that did
4405/// not support named parameters they would be ignored on the macro definition.
4406/// But to support both styles of parameters this is not possible so if a macro
4407/// definition has named parameters but does not use them and has what appears
4408/// to be positional parameters, strings like $1, $2, ... and $n, then issue a
4409/// warning that the positional parameter found in body which have no effect.
4410/// Hoping the developer will either remove the named parameters from the macro
4411/// definition so the positional parameters get used if that was what was
4412/// intended or change the macro to use the named parameters. It is possible
4413/// this warning will trigger when the none of the named parameters are used
4414/// and the strings like $1 are infact to simply to be passed trough unchanged.
4415void AsmParser::checkForBadMacro(SMLoc DirectiveLoc, StringRef Name,
4416 StringRef Body,
4417 ArrayRef<MCAsmMacroParameter> Parameters) {
4418 // If this macro is not defined with named parameters the warning we are
4419 // checking for here doesn't apply.
4420 unsigned NParameters = Parameters.size();
4421 if (NParameters == 0)
4422 return;
4423
4424 bool NamedParametersFound = false;
4425 bool PositionalParametersFound = false;
4426
4427 // Look at the body of the macro for use of both the named parameters and what
4428 // are likely to be positional parameters. This is what expandMacro() is
4429 // doing when it finds the parameters in the body.
4430 while (!Body.empty()) {
4431 // Scan for the next possible parameter.
4432 std::size_t End = Body.size(), Pos = 0;
4433 for (; Pos != End; ++Pos) {
4434 // Check for a substitution or escape.
4435 // This macro is defined with parameters, look for \foo, \bar, etc.
4436 if (Body[Pos] == '\\' && Pos + 1 != End)
4437 break;
4438
4439 // This macro should have parameters, but look for $0, $1, ..., $n too.
4440 if (Body[Pos] != '$' || Pos + 1 == End)
4441 continue;
4442 char Next = Body[Pos + 1];
4443 if (Next == '$' || Next == 'n' ||
4444 isdigit(static_cast<unsigned char>(Next)))
4445 break;
4446 }
4447
4448 // Check if we reached the end.
4449 if (Pos == End)
4450 break;
4451
4452 if (Body[Pos] == '$') {
4453 switch (Body[Pos + 1]) {
4454 // $$ => $
4455 case '$':
4456 break;
4457
4458 // $n => number of arguments
4459 case 'n':
4460 PositionalParametersFound = true;
4461 break;
4462
4463 // $[0-9] => argument
4464 default: {
4465 PositionalParametersFound = true;
4466 break;
4467 }
4468 }
4469 Pos += 2;
4470 } else {
4471 unsigned I = Pos + 1;
4472 while (isIdentifierChar(Body[I]) && I + 1 != End)
4473 ++I;
4474
4475 const char *Begin = Body.data() + Pos + 1;
4476 StringRef Argument(Begin, I - (Pos + 1));
4477 unsigned Index = 0;
4478 for (; Index < NParameters; ++Index)
4479 if (Parameters[Index].Name == Argument)
4480 break;
4481
4482 if (Index == NParameters) {
4483 if (Body[Pos + 1] == '(' && Body[Pos + 2] == ')')
4484 Pos += 3;
4485 else {
4486 Pos = I;
4487 }
4488 } else {
4489 NamedParametersFound = true;
4490 Pos += 1 + Argument.size();
4491 }
4492 }
4493 // Update the scan point.
4494 Body = Body.substr(Pos);
4495 }
4496
4497 if (!NamedParametersFound && PositionalParametersFound)
4498 Warning(DirectiveLoc, "macro defined with named parameters which are not "
4499 "used in macro body, possible positional parameter "
4500 "found in body which will have no effect");
4501}

4503/// parseDirectiveExitMacro
4504/// ::= .exitm
4505bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveExitMacro(StringRef Directive) {
4506 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
4507 "unexpected token in '" + Directive + "' directive"))
4508 return true;
4509
4510 if (!isInsideMacroInstantiation())
4511 return TokError("unexpected '" + Directive + "' in file, "
4512 "no current macro definition");
4513
4514 // Exit all conditionals that are active in the current macro.
4515 while (TheCondStack.size() != ActiveMacros.back()->CondStackDepth) {
4516 TheCondState = TheCondStack.back();
4517 TheCondStack.pop_back();
4518 }
4519
4520 handleMacroExit();
4521 return false;
4522}

4525/// ::= .endm
4526/// ::= .endmacro
4527bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveEndMacro(StringRef Directive) {
4528 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
4529 return TokError("unexpected token in '" + Directive + "' directive");
4530

4532 // instantiation.
4533 if (isInsideMacroInstantiation()) {
4534 handleMacroExit();
4535 return false;
4536 }
4537
4538 // Otherwise, this .endmacro is a stray entry in the file; well formed
4539 // .endmacro directives are handled during the macro definition parsing.
4540 return TokError("unexpected '" + Directive + "' in file, "
4541 "no current macro definition");

4586/// parseDirectiveBundleLock
4587/// ::= {.bundle_lock} [align_to_end]
4588bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveBundleLock() {
4589 if (checkForValidSection())
4590 return true;
4591 bool AlignToEnd = false;
4592
4593 StringRef Option;
4594 SMLoc Loc = getTok().getLoc();
4595 const char *kInvalidOptionError =
4596 "invalid option for '.bundle_lock' directive";
4597
4598 if (!parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
4599 if (check(parseIdentifier(Option), Loc, kInvalidOptionError) ||
4600 check(Option != "align_to_end", Loc, kInvalidOptionError) ||
4601 parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
4602 "unexpected token after '.bundle_lock' directive option"))
4603 return true;
4604 AlignToEnd = true;
4605 }
4606
4607 getStreamer().EmitBundleLock(AlignToEnd);
4608 return false;
4609}

4644/// parseDirectiveDCB
4645/// ::= .dcb.{b, l, w} expression, expression
4646bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveDCB(StringRef IDVal, unsigned Size) {
4647 SMLoc NumValuesLoc = Lexer.getLoc();
4648 int64_t NumValues;
4649 if (checkForValidSection() || parseAbsoluteExpression(NumValues))
4650 return true;
4651
4652 if (NumValues < 0) {
4653 Warning(NumValuesLoc, "'" + Twine(IDVal) + "' directive with negative repeat count has no effect");
4654 return false;
4655 }
4656
4657 if (parseToken(AsmToken::Comma,
4658 "unexpected token in '" + Twine(IDVal) + "' directive"))
4659 return true;
4660
4661 const MCExpr *Value;
4662 SMLoc ExprLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
4663 if (parseExpression(Value))
4664 return true;
4665
4666 // Special case constant expressions to match code generator.
4667 if (const MCConstantExpr *MCE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Value)) {
4668 assert(Size <= 8 && "Invalid size");
4669 uint64_t IntValue = MCE->getValue();
4670 if (!isUIntN(8 * Size, IntValue) && !isIntN(8 * Size, IntValue))
4671 return Error(ExprLoc, "literal value out of range for directive");
4672 for (uint64_t i = 0, e = NumValues; i != e; ++i)
4673 getStreamer().EmitIntValue(IntValue, Size);
4674 } else {
4675 for (uint64_t i = 0, e = NumValues; i != e; ++i)
4676 getStreamer().EmitValue(Value, Size, ExprLoc);
4677 }
4678
4679 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
4680 "unexpected token in '" + Twine(IDVal) + "' directive"))
4681 return true;
4682
4683 return false;
4684}

4741/// parseDirectiveLEB128

4745 return true;

4750 return true;

4754 getStreamer().EmitULEB128Value(Value);

4764/// parseDirectiveSymbolAttribute
4765/// ::= { ".globl", ".weak", ... } [ identifier ( , identifier )* ]
4766bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveSymbolAttribute(MCSymbolAttr Attr) {
4767 auto parseOp = [&]() -> bool {
4768 StringRef Name;
4769 SMLoc Loc = getTok().getLoc();
4770 if (parseIdentifier(Name))
4771 return Error(Loc, "expected identifier");
4772 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Name);
4773

4775 if (Sym->isTemporary())

4788/// parseDirectiveComm
4789/// ::= ( .comm | .lcomm ) identifier , size_expression [ , align_expression ]
4790bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveComm(bool IsLocal) {
4791 if (checkForValidSection())
4792 return true;
4793
4794 SMLoc IDLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
4795 StringRef Name;
4796 if (parseIdentifier(Name))
4797 return TokError("expected identifier in directive");
4798
4799 // Handle the identifier as the key symbol.
4800 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Name);
4801
4802 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Comma))
4803 return TokError("unexpected token in directive");
4804 Lex();
4805
4806 int64_t Size;
4807 SMLoc SizeLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
4808 if (parseAbsoluteExpression(Size))
4809 return true;
4810
4811 int64_t Pow2Alignment = 0;
4812 SMLoc Pow2AlignmentLoc;
4813 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Comma)) {
4814 Lex();
4815 Pow2AlignmentLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
4816 if (parseAbsoluteExpression(Pow2Alignment))
4817 return true;
4818
4819 LCOMM::LCOMMType LCOMM = Lexer.getMAI().getLCOMMDirectiveAlignmentType();
4820 if (IsLocal && LCOMM == LCOMM::NoAlignment)
4821 return Error(Pow2AlignmentLoc, "alignment not supported on this target");
4822
4823 // If this target takes alignments in bytes (not log) validate and convert.
4824 if ((!IsLocal && Lexer.getMAI().getCOMMDirectiveAlignmentIsInBytes()) ||
4825 (IsLocal && LCOMM == LCOMM::ByteAlignment)) {
4826 if (!isPowerOf2_64(Pow2Alignment))
4827 return Error(Pow2AlignmentLoc, "alignment must be a power of 2");
4828 Pow2Alignment = Log2_64(Pow2Alignment);
4829 }
4830 }
4831
4832 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
4833 "unexpected token in '.comm' or '.lcomm' directive"))
4834 return true;
4835
4836 // NOTE: a size of zero for a .comm should create a undefined symbol
4837 // but a size of .lcomm creates a bss symbol of size zero.
4838 if (Size < 0)
4839 return Error(SizeLoc, "invalid '.comm' or '.lcomm' directive size, can't "
4840 "be less than zero");
4841
4842 // NOTE: The alignment in the directive is a power of 2 value, the assembler
4843 // may internally end up wanting an alignment in bytes.
4844 // FIXME: Diagnose overflow.
4845 if (Pow2Alignment < 0)
4846 return Error(Pow2AlignmentLoc, "invalid '.comm' or '.lcomm' directive "
4847 "alignment, can't be less than zero");
4848
4849 Sym->redefineIfPossible();
4850 if (!Sym->isUndefined())
4851 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid symbol redefinition of " + Sym->getName());
4852
4853 // Create the Symbol as a common or local common with Size and Pow2Alignment
4854 if (IsLocal) {
4855 getStreamer().EmitLocalCommonSymbol(Sym, Size, 1 << Pow2Alignment,
4856 TailPaddingAmount::None);
4857 return false;
4858 }
4859
4860 getStreamer().EmitCommonSymbol(Sym, Size, 1 << Pow2Alignment,
4861 TailPaddingAmount::None);
4862 return false;
4863}

4885/// parseDirectiveInclude
4886/// ::= .include "filename"
4887bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveInclude() {
4888 // Allow the strings to have escaped octal character sequence.
4889 std::string Filename;
4890 SMLoc IncludeLoc = getTok().getLoc();
4891
4892 if (check(getTok().isNot(AsmToken::String),
4893 "expected string in '.include' directive") ||
4894 parseEscapedString(Filename) ||
4895 check(getTok().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement),
4896 "unexpected token in '.include' directive") ||
4897 // Attempt to switch the lexer to the included file before consuming the
4898 // end of statement to avoid losing it when we switch.
4899 check(enterIncludeFile(Filename), IncludeLoc,
4900 "Could not find include file '" + Filename + "'"))
4901 return true;
4902
4903 return false;
4904}

4906/// parseDirectiveIncbin
4907/// ::= .incbin "filename" [ , skip [ , count ] ]
4908bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveIncbin() {
4909 // Allow the strings to have escaped octal character sequence.
4910 std::string Filename;
4911 SMLoc IncbinLoc = getTok().getLoc();
4912 if (check(getTok().isNot(AsmToken::String),
4913 "expected string in '.incbin' directive") ||
4914 parseEscapedString(Filename))
4915 return true;
4916
4917 int64_t Skip = 0;
4918 const MCExpr *Count = nullptr;
4919 SMLoc SkipLoc, CountLoc;
4920 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma)) {
4921 // The skip expression can be omitted while specifying the count, e.g:
4922 // .incbin "filename",,4
4923 if (getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Comma)) {
4924 if (parseTokenLoc(SkipLoc) || parseAbsoluteExpression(Skip))
4925 return true;
4926 }
4927 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma)) {
4928 CountLoc = getTok().getLoc();
4929 if (parseExpression(Count))
4930 return true;
4931 }
4932 }
4933
4934 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
4935 "unexpected token in '.incbin' directive"))
4936 return true;
4937
4938 if (check(Skip < 0, SkipLoc, "skip is negative"))
4939 return true;
4940
4941 // Attempt to process the included file.
4942 if (processIncbinFile(Filename, Skip, Count, CountLoc))
4943 return Error(IncbinLoc, "Could not find incbin file '" + Filename + "'");
4944 return false;
4945}

4947/// parseDirectiveIf
4948/// ::= .if{,eq,ge,gt,le,lt,ne} expression
4949bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveIf(SMLoc DirectiveLoc, DirectiveKind DirKind) {
4950 TheCondStack.push_back(TheCondState);
4951 TheCondState.TheCond = AsmCond::IfCond;
4952 if (TheCondState.Ignore) {
4953 eatToEndOfStatement();
4954 } else {
4955 int64_t ExprValue;
4956 if (parseAbsoluteExpression(ExprValue) ||
4957 parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
4958 "unexpected token in '.if' directive"))
4959 return true;
4960
4961 switch (DirKind) {
4962 default:
4963 llvm_unreachable("unsupported directive");
4964 case DK_IF:
4965 case DK_IFNE:
4966 break;
4967 case DK_IFEQ:
4968 ExprValue = ExprValue == 0;
4969 break;
4970 case DK_IFGE:
4971 ExprValue = ExprValue >= 0;
4972 break;
4973 case DK_IFGT:
4974 ExprValue = ExprValue > 0;
4975 break;
4976 case DK_IFLE:
4977 ExprValue = ExprValue <= 0;
4978 break;
4979 case DK_IFLT:
4980 ExprValue = ExprValue < 0;
4981 break;
4982 }
4983
4984 TheCondState.CondMet = ExprValue;
4985 TheCondState.Ignore = !TheCondState.CondMet;
4986 }
4987
4988 return false;
4989}

5079/// parseDirectiveIfdef
5080/// ::= .ifdef symbol
5081bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveIfdef(SMLoc DirectiveLoc, bool expect_defined) {
5082 StringRef Name;
5083 TheCondStack.push_back(TheCondState);
5084 TheCondState.TheCond = AsmCond::IfCond;
5085
5086 if (TheCondState.Ignore) {
5087 eatToEndOfStatement();

5090 parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement, "unexpected token in '.ifdef'"))
5091 return true;

5099 TheCondState.Ignore = !TheCondState.CondMet;

5105/// parseDirectiveElseIf
5106/// ::= .elseif expression
5107bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveElseIf(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
5108 if (TheCondState.TheCond != AsmCond::IfCond &&
5109 TheCondState.TheCond != AsmCond::ElseIfCond)
5110 return Error(DirectiveLoc, "Encountered a .elseif that doesn't follow an"
5111 " .if or an .elseif");
5112 TheCondState.TheCond = AsmCond::ElseIfCond;
5113
5114 bool LastIgnoreState = false;
5115 if (!TheCondStack.empty())
5116 LastIgnoreState = TheCondStack.back().Ignore;
5117 if (LastIgnoreState || TheCondState.CondMet) {
5118 TheCondState.Ignore = true;
5119 eatToEndOfStatement();
5120 } else {
5121 int64_t ExprValue;
5122 if (parseAbsoluteExpression(ExprValue))
5123 return true;
5124
5125 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
5126 "unexpected token in '.elseif' directive"))
5127 return true;
5128
5129 TheCondState.CondMet = ExprValue;
5130 TheCondState.Ignore = !TheCondState.CondMet;
5131 }
5132
5133 return false;
5134}

5137/// ::= .else
5138bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveElse(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
5139 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
5140 "unexpected token in '.else' directive"))
5141 return true;
5142
5143 if (TheCondState.TheCond != AsmCond::IfCond &&
5144 TheCondState.TheCond != AsmCond::ElseIfCond)
5145 return Error(DirectiveLoc, "Encountered a .else that doesn't follow "
5146 " an .if or an .elseif");
5147 TheCondState.TheCond = AsmCond::ElseCond;
5148 bool LastIgnoreState = false;
5149 if (!TheCondStack.empty())
5150 LastIgnoreState = TheCondStack.back().Ignore;
5151 if (LastIgnoreState || TheCondState.CondMet)
5152 TheCondState.Ignore = true;
5153 else
5154 TheCondState.Ignore = false;

5172/// parseDirectiveError
5173/// ::= .err
5174/// ::= .error [string]
5175bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveError(SMLoc L, bool WithMessage) {
5176 if (!TheCondStack.empty()) {
5177 if (TheCondStack.back().Ignore) {
5178 eatToEndOfStatement();
5179 return false;
5180 }
5181 }
5182
5183 if (!WithMessage)
5184 return Error(L, ".err encountered");
5185
5186 StringRef Message = ".error directive invoked in source file";
5187 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
5188 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::String))
5189 return TokError(".error argument must be a string");
5190
5191 Message = getTok().getStringContents();
5192 Lex();
5193 }
5194
5195 return Error(L, Message);

5203 eatToEndOfStatement();
5204 return false;

5206 }
5207
5208 StringRef Message = ".warning directive invoked in source file";
5209
5210 if (!parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
5211 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::String))
5212 return TokError(".warning argument must be a string");
5213
5214 Message = getTok().getStringContents();
5215 Lex();
5216 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
5217 "expected end of statement in '.warning' directive"))
5218 return true;

5404
5405MCAsmMacro *AsmParser::parseMacroLikeBody(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
5406 AsmToken EndToken, StartToken = getTok();
5407
5408 unsigned NestLevel = 0;
5409 while (true) {
5410 // Check whether we have reached the end of the file.
5411 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Eof)) {
5412 printError(DirectiveLoc, "no matching '.endr' in definition");
5413 return nullptr;
5414 }
5415
5416 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Identifier) &&
5417 (getTok().getIdentifier() == ".rep" ||
5418 getTok().getIdentifier() == ".rept" ||
5419 getTok().getIdentifier() == ".irp" ||
5420 getTok().getIdentifier() == ".irpc")) {
5421 ++NestLevel;
5422 }
5423
5424 // Otherwise, check whether we have reached the .endr.
5425 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Identifier) && getTok().getIdentifier() == ".endr") {
5426 if (NestLevel == 0) {
5427 EndToken = getTok();
5428 Lex();
5429 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
5430 printError(getTok().getLoc(),
5431 "unexpected token in '.endr' directive");
5432 return nullptr;
5433 }
5434 break;
5435 }
5436 --NestLevel;
5437 }
5438
5439 // Otherwise, scan till the end of the statement.
5440 eatToEndOfStatement();
5441 }
5442
5443 const char *BodyStart = StartToken.getLoc().getPointer();
5444 const char *BodyEnd = EndToken.getLoc().getPointer();
5445 StringRef Body = StringRef(BodyStart, BodyEnd - BodyStart);
5446
5447 // We Are Anonymous.
5448 MacroLikeBodies.emplace_back(StringRef(), Body, MCAsmMacroParameters());
5449 return &MacroLikeBodies.back();
5450}
5451
5452void AsmParser::instantiateMacroLikeBody(MCAsmMacro *M, SMLoc DirectiveLoc,
5453 raw_svector_ostream &OS) {
5454 OS << ".endr\n";
5455
5456 std::unique_ptr<MemoryBuffer> Instantiation =
5457 MemoryBuffer::getMemBufferCopy(OS.str(), "<instantiation>");
5458
5459 // Create the macro instantiation object and add to the current macro
5460 // instantiation stack.
5461 MacroInstantiation *MI = new MacroInstantiation(
5462 DirectiveLoc, CurBuffer, getTok().getLoc(), TheCondStack.size());
5463 ActiveMacros.push_back(MI);
5464
5465 // Jump to the macro instantiation and prime the lexer.
5466 CurBuffer = SrcMgr.AddNewSourceBuffer(std::move(Instantiation), SMLoc());
5467 Lexer.setBuffer(SrcMgr.getMemoryBuffer(CurBuffer)->getBuffer());
5468 Lex();
5469}
5470
5471/// parseDirectiveRept
5472/// ::= .rep | .rept count
5473bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveRept(SMLoc DirectiveLoc, StringRef Dir) {
5474 const MCExpr *CountExpr;
5475 SMLoc CountLoc = getTok().getLoc();
5476 if (parseExpression(CountExpr))
5477 return true;
5478
5479 int64_t Count;
5480 if (!CountExpr->evaluateAsAbsolute(Count, getStreamer().getAssemblerPtr())) {
5481 return Error(CountLoc, "unexpected token in '" + Dir + "' directive");
5482 }
5483
5484 if (check(Count < 0, CountLoc, "Count is negative") ||
5485 parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
5486 "unexpected token in '" + Dir + "' directive"))
5487 return true;
5488
5489 // Lex the rept definition.
5490 MCAsmMacro *M = parseMacroLikeBody(DirectiveLoc);
5491 if (!M)
5492 return true;
5493
5494 // Macro instantiation is lexical, unfortunately. We construct a new buffer
5495 // to hold the macro body with substitutions.
5496 SmallString<256> Buf;
5497 raw_svector_ostream OS(Buf);
5498 while (Count--) {
5499 // Note that the AtPseudoVariable is disabled for instantiations of .rep(t).
5500 if (expandMacro(OS, M->Body, None, None, false, getTok().getLoc()))
5501 return true;
5502 }
5503 instantiateMacroLikeBody(M, DirectiveLoc, OS);
5504
5505 return false;
5506}
5507
5508/// parseDirectiveIrp
5509/// ::= .irp symbol,values
5510bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveIrp(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
5511 MCAsmMacroParameter Parameter;
5512 MCAsmMacroArguments A;
5513 if (check(parseIdentifier(Parameter.Name),
5514 "expected identifier in '.irp' directive") ||
5515 parseToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected comma in '.irp' directive") ||
5516 parseMacroArguments(nullptr, A) ||
5517 parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement, "expected End of Statement"))
5518 return true;
5519
5520 // Lex the irp definition.
5521 MCAsmMacro *M = parseMacroLikeBody(DirectiveLoc);
5522 if (!M)
5523 return true;
5524
5525 // Macro instantiation is lexical, unfortunately. We construct a new buffer
5526 // to hold the macro body with substitutions.
5527 SmallString<256> Buf;
5528 raw_svector_ostream OS(Buf);
5529
5530 for (const MCAsmMacroArgument &Arg : A) {
5531 // Note that the AtPseudoVariable is enabled for instantiations of .irp.
5532 // This is undocumented, but GAS seems to support it.
5533 if (expandMacro(OS, M->Body, Parameter, Arg, true, getTok().getLoc()))
5534 return true;
5535 }
5536
5537 instantiateMacroLikeBody(M, DirectiveLoc, OS);
5538
5539 return false;
5540}
5541
5542/// parseDirectiveIrpc
5543/// ::= .irpc symbol,values
5544bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveIrpc(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
5545 MCAsmMacroParameter Parameter;
5546 MCAsmMacroArguments A;
5547
5548 if (check(parseIdentifier(Parameter.Name),
5549 "expected identifier in '.irpc' directive") ||
5550 parseToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected comma in '.irpc' directive") ||
5551 parseMacroArguments(nullptr, A))
5552 return true;
5553
5554 if (A.size() != 1 || A.front().size() != 1)
5555 return TokError("unexpected token in '.irpc' directive");
5556
5557 // Eat the end of statement.
5558 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement, "expected end of statement"))
5559 return true;
5560
5561 // Lex the irpc definition.
5562 MCAsmMacro *M = parseMacroLikeBody(DirectiveLoc);
5563 if (!M)
5564 return true;
5565
5566 // Macro instantiation is lexical, unfortunately. We construct a new buffer
5567 // to hold the macro body with substitutions.
5568 SmallString<256> Buf;
5569 raw_svector_ostream OS(Buf);
5570
5571 StringRef Values = A.front().front().getString();
5572 for (std::size_t I = 0, End = Values.size(); I != End; ++I) {
5573 MCAsmMacroArgument Arg;
5574 Arg.emplace_back(AsmToken::Identifier, Values.slice(I, I + 1));
5575
5576 // Note that the AtPseudoVariable is enabled for instantiations of .irpc.
5577 // This is undocumented, but GAS seems to support it.
5578 if (expandMacro(OS, M->Body, Parameter, Arg, true, getTok().getLoc()))
5579 return true;
5580 }
5581
5582 instantiateMacroLikeBody(M, DirectiveLoc, OS);
5583
5584 return false;
5585}
5586
5587bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveEndr(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
5588 if (ActiveMacros.empty())
5589 return TokError("unmatched '.endr' directive");
5590
5591 // The only .repl that should get here are the ones created by
5592 // instantiateMacroLikeBody.
5593 assert(getLexer().is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement));
5594
5595 handleMacroExit();
5596 return false;
5597}

5599bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveMSEmit(SMLoc IDLoc, ParseStatementInfo &Info,
5600 size_t Len) {
5601 const MCExpr *Value;
5602 SMLoc ExprLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
5603 if (parseExpression(Value))
5604 return true;
5605 const MCConstantExpr *MCE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Value);
5606 if (!MCE)
5607 return Error(ExprLoc, "unexpected expression in _emit");
5608 uint64_t IntValue = MCE->getValue();
5609 if (!isUInt<8>(IntValue) && !isInt<8>(IntValue))
5610 return Error(ExprLoc, "literal value out of range for directive");
5611
5612 Info.AsmRewrites->emplace_back(AOK_Emit, IDLoc, Len);
5613 return false;
5614}

5616bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveMSAlign(SMLoc IDLoc, ParseStatementInfo &Info) {
5617 const MCExpr *Value;
5618 SMLoc ExprLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
5619 if (parseExpression(Value))
5620 return true;
5621 const MCConstantExpr *MCE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Value);
5622 if (!MCE)
5623 return Error(ExprLoc, "unexpected expression in align");
5624 uint64_t IntValue = MCE->getValue();
5625 if (!isPowerOf2_64(IntValue))
5626 return Error(ExprLoc, "literal value not a power of two greater then zero");
5627
5628 Info.AsmRewrites->emplace_back(AOK_Align, IDLoc, 5, Log2_64(IntValue));
5629 return false;
5630}

5658/// parseDirectiveCheriCap
5659/// ::= .chericap sym[+off]
5660bool AsmParser::parseDirectiveCheriCap(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
5661 const MCExpr *SymExpr;
5662 SMLoc ExprLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
5663
5664 if (!getTargetParser().isCheri())
5665 return Error(DirectiveLoc, "'.chericap' requires CHERI");
5666
5667 if (parseExpression(SymExpr))
5668 return true;
5669
5670 int64_t Offset = 0;
5671 unsigned CapSize = getTargetParser().getCheriCapabilitySize();
5672 // Allow .chericap 0x123456 to create an untagged uintcap_t
5673 if (SymExpr->evaluateAsAbsolute(Offset)) {
5674 getStreamer().EmitCheriIntcap(Offset, CapSize, ExprLoc);
5675 } else {
5676 const MCSymbolRefExpr *SRE = nullptr;
5677 if (const MCBinaryExpr *BE = dyn_cast<MCBinaryExpr>(SymExpr)) {
5678 const MCConstantExpr *CE = nullptr;
5679 bool Neg = false;
5680 switch (BE->getOpcode()) {
5681 case MCBinaryExpr::Sub:
5682 Neg = true;
5683 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5684 case MCBinaryExpr::Add:
5685 CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(BE->getRHS());
5686 break;
5687 default:
5688 break;
5689 }
5690
5691 SRE = dyn_cast<MCSymbolRefExpr>(BE->getLHS());
5692 if (!SRE || !CE)
5693 return Error(ExprLoc, "must be sym[+const]");
5694 Offset = CE->getValue();
5695 if (Neg)
5696 Offset = -Offset;
5697 } else {
5698 SRE = dyn_cast<MCSymbolRefExpr>(SymExpr);
5699 if (!SRE)
5700 return Error(ExprLoc, "must be sym[+const]");
5701 Offset = 0;
5702 }
5703 const MCSymbol &Symbol = SRE->getSymbol();
5704 getStreamer().EmitCheriCapability(&Symbol, Offset, CapSize, ExprLoc);
5705 }
5706 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement, "expected end of statement"))
5707 return true;
5708 return false;
5709}
5710
5711// We are comparing pointers, but the pointers are relative to a single string.
5712// Thus, this should always be deterministic.
5713static int rewritesSort(const AsmRewrite *AsmRewriteA,
5714 const AsmRewrite *AsmRewriteB) {
5715 if (AsmRewriteA->Loc.getPointer() < AsmRewriteB->Loc.getPointer())
5716 return -1;
5717 if (AsmRewriteB->Loc.getPointer() < AsmRewriteA->Loc.getPointer())
5718 return 1;
5719
5720 // It's possible to have a SizeDirective, Imm/ImmPrefix and an Input/Output
5721 // rewrite to the same location. Make sure the SizeDirective rewrite is
5722 // performed first, then the Imm/ImmPrefix and finally the Input/Output. This
5723 // ensures the sort algorithm is stable.
5724 if (AsmRewritePrecedence[AsmRewriteA->Kind] >
5725 AsmRewritePrecedence[AsmRewriteB->Kind])
5726 return -1;
5727
5728 if (AsmRewritePrecedence[AsmRewriteA->Kind] <
5729 AsmRewritePrecedence[AsmRewriteB->Kind])
5730 return 1;
5731 llvm_unreachable("Unstable rewrite sort.");
5732}
5733
5734bool AsmParser::parseMSInlineAsm(
5735 void *AsmLoc, std::string &AsmString, unsigned &NumOutputs,
5736 unsigned &NumInputs, SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<void *, bool>> &OpDecls,
5737 SmallVectorImpl<std::string> &Constraints,
5738 SmallVectorImpl<std::string> &Clobbers, const MCInstrInfo *MII,
5739 const MCInstPrinter *IP, MCAsmParserSemaCallback &SI) {
5740 SmallVector<void *, 4> InputDecls;
5741 SmallVector<void *, 4> OutputDecls;
5742 SmallVector<bool, 4> InputDeclsAddressOf;
5743 SmallVector<bool, 4> OutputDeclsAddressOf;
5744 SmallVector<std::string, 4> InputConstraints;
5745 SmallVector<std::string, 4> OutputConstraints;
5746 SmallVector<unsigned, 4> ClobberRegs;
5747
5748 SmallVector<AsmRewrite, 4> AsmStrRewrites;
5749
5750 // Prime the lexer.
5751 Lex();
5752
5753 // While we have input, parse each statement.
5754 unsigned InputIdx = 0;
5755 unsigned OutputIdx = 0;
5756 while (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Eof)) {
5757 // Parse curly braces marking block start/end
5758 if (parseCurlyBlockScope(AsmStrRewrites))
5759 continue;
5760
5761 ParseStatementInfo Info(&AsmStrRewrites);
5762 bool StatementErr = parseStatement(Info, &SI);
5763
5764 if (StatementErr || Info.ParseError) {
5765 // Emit pending errors if any exist.
5766 printPendingErrors();
5767 return true;
5768 }
5769
5770 // No pending error should exist here.
5771 assert(!hasPendingError() && "unexpected error from parseStatement");
5772
5773 if (Info.Opcode == ~0U)
5774 continue;
5775
5776 const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII->get(Info.Opcode);
5777
5778 // Build the list of clobbers, outputs and inputs.
5779 for (unsigned i = 1, e = Info.ParsedOperands.size(); i != e; ++i) {
5780 MCParsedAsmOperand &Operand = *Info.ParsedOperands[i];
5781
5782 // Immediate.
5783 if (Operand.isImm())
5784 continue;
5785
5786 // Register operand.
5787 if (Operand.isReg() && !Operand.needAddressOf() &&
5788 !getTargetParser().OmitRegisterFromClobberLists(Operand.getReg())) {
5789 unsigned NumDefs = Desc.getNumDefs();
5790 // Clobber.
5791 if (NumDefs && Operand.getMCOperandNum() < NumDefs)
5792 ClobberRegs.push_back(Operand.getReg());
5793 continue;
5794 }
5795
5796 // Expr/Input or Output.
5797 StringRef SymName = Operand.getSymName();
5798 if (SymName.empty())
5799 continue;
5800
5801 void *OpDecl = Operand.getOpDecl();
5802 if (!OpDecl)
5803 continue;
5804
5805 bool isOutput = (i == 1) && Desc.mayStore();
5806 SMLoc Start = SMLoc::getFromPointer(SymName.data());
5807 if (isOutput) {
5808 ++InputIdx;
5809 OutputDecls.push_back(OpDecl);
5810 OutputDeclsAddressOf.push_back(Operand.needAddressOf());
5811 OutputConstraints.push_back(("=" + Operand.getConstraint()).str());
5812 AsmStrRewrites.emplace_back(AOK_Output, Start, SymName.size());
5813 } else {
5814 InputDecls.push_back(OpDecl);
5815 InputDeclsAddressOf.push_back(Operand.needAddressOf());
5816 InputConstraints.push_back(Operand.getConstraint().str());
5817 AsmStrRewrites.emplace_back(AOK_Input, Start, SymName.size());
5818 }
5819 }
5820
5821 // Consider implicit defs to be clobbers. Think of cpuid and push.
5822 ArrayRef<MCPhysReg> ImpDefs(Desc.getImplicitDefs(),
5823 Desc.getNumImplicitDefs());
5824 ClobberRegs.insert(ClobberRegs.end(), ImpDefs.begin(), ImpDefs.end());
5825 }
5826
5827 // Set the number of Outputs and Inputs.
5828 NumOutputs = OutputDecls.size();
5829 NumInputs = InputDecls.size();
5830
5831 // Set the unique clobbers.
5832 array_pod_sort(ClobberRegs.begin(), ClobberRegs.end());
5833 ClobberRegs.erase(std::unique(ClobberRegs.begin(), ClobberRegs.end()),
5834 ClobberRegs.end());
5835 Clobbers.assign(ClobberRegs.size(), std::string());
5836 for (unsigned I = 0, E = ClobberRegs.size(); I != E; ++I) {
5837 raw_string_ostream OS(Clobbers[I]);
5838 IP->printRegName(OS, ClobberRegs[I]);
5839 }
5840
5841 // Merge the various outputs and inputs. Output are expected first.
5842 if (NumOutputs || NumInputs) {
5843 unsigned NumExprs = NumOutputs + NumInputs;
5844 OpDecls.resize(NumExprs);
5845 Constraints.resize(NumExprs);
5846 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumOutputs; ++i) {
5847 OpDecls[i] = std::make_pair(OutputDecls[i], OutputDeclsAddressOf[i]);
5848 Constraints[i] = OutputConstraints[i];
5849 }
5850 for (unsigned i = 0, j = NumOutputs; i < NumInputs; ++i, ++j) {
5851 OpDecls[j] = std::make_pair(InputDecls[i], InputDeclsAddressOf[i]);
5852 Constraints[j] = InputConstraints[i];
5853 }
5854 }
5855
5856 // Build the IR assembly string.
5857 std::string AsmStringIR;
5858 raw_string_ostream OS(AsmStringIR);
5859 StringRef ASMString =
5860 SrcMgr.getMemoryBuffer(SrcMgr.getMainFileID())->getBuffer();
5861 const char *AsmStart = ASMString.begin();
5862 const char *AsmEnd = ASMString.end();
5863 array_pod_sort(AsmStrRewrites.begin(), AsmStrRewrites.end(), rewritesSort);
5864 for (const AsmRewrite &AR : AsmStrRewrites) {
5865 AsmRewriteKind Kind = AR.Kind;
5866
5867 const char *Loc = AR.Loc.getPointer();
5868 assert(Loc >= AsmStart && "Expected Loc to be at or after Start!");
5869
5870 // Emit everything up to the immediate/expression.
5871 if (unsigned Len = Loc - AsmStart)
5872 OS << StringRef(AsmStart, Len);
5873
5874 // Skip the original expression.
5875 if (Kind == AOK_Skip) {
5876 AsmStart = Loc + AR.Len;
5877 continue;
5878 }
5879
5880 unsigned AdditionalSkip = 0;
5881 // Rewrite expressions in $N notation.
5882 switch (Kind) {
5883 default:
5884 break;
5885 case AOK_IntelExpr:
5886 assert(AR.IntelExp.isValid() && "cannot write invalid intel expression");
5887 if (AR.IntelExp.NeedBracs)
5888 OS << "[";
5889 if (AR.IntelExp.hasBaseReg())
5890 OS << AR.IntelExp.BaseReg;
5891 if (AR.IntelExp.hasIndexReg())
5892 OS << (AR.IntelExp.hasBaseReg() ? " + " : "")
5893 << AR.IntelExp.IndexReg;
5894 if (AR.IntelExp.Scale > 1)
5895 OS << " * $$" << AR.IntelExp.Scale;
5896 if (AR.IntelExp.Imm || !AR.IntelExp.hasRegs())
5897 OS << (AR.IntelExp.hasRegs() ? " + $$" : "$$") << AR.IntelExp.Imm;
5898 if (AR.IntelExp.NeedBracs)
5899 OS << "]";
5900 break;
5901 case AOK_Label:
5902 OS << Ctx.getAsmInfo()->getPrivateLabelPrefix() << AR.Label;
5903 break;
5904 case AOK_Input:
5905 OS << '$' << InputIdx++;
5906 break;
5907 case AOK_Output:
5908 OS << '$' << OutputIdx++;
5909 break;
5910 case AOK_SizeDirective:
5911 switch (AR.Val) {
5912 default: break;
5913 case 8: OS << "byte ptr "; break;
5914 case 16: OS << "word ptr "; break;
5915 case 32: OS << "dword ptr "; break;
5916 case 64: OS << "qword ptr "; break;
5917 case 80: OS << "xword ptr "; break;
5918 case 128: OS << "xmmword ptr "; break;
5919 case 256: OS << "ymmword ptr "; break;
5920 }
5921 break;
5922 case AOK_Emit:
5923 OS << ".byte";
5924 break;
5925 case AOK_Align: {
5926 // MS alignment directives are measured in bytes. If the native assembler
5927 // measures alignment in bytes, we can pass it straight through.
5928 OS << ".align";
5929 if (getContext().getAsmInfo()->getAlignmentIsInBytes())
5930 break;
5931
5932 // Alignment is in log2 form, so print that instead and skip the original
5933 // immediate.
5934 unsigned Val = AR.Val;
5935 OS << ' ' << Val;
5936 assert(Val < 10 && "Expected alignment less then 2^10.");
5937 AdditionalSkip = (Val < 4) ? 2 : Val < 7 ? 3 : 4;
5938 break;
5939 }
5940 case AOK_EVEN:
5941 OS << ".even";
5942 break;
5943 case AOK_EndOfStatement:
5944 OS << "\n\t";
5945 break;
5946 }
5947
5948 // Skip the original expression.
5949 AsmStart = Loc + AR.Len + AdditionalSkip;
5950 }
5951
5952 // Emit the remainder of the asm string.
5953 if (AsmStart != AsmEnd)
5954 OS << StringRef(AsmStart, AsmEnd - AsmStart);
5955
5956 AsmString = OS.str();
5957 return false;
5958}

5963/// Returns whether the given symbol is used anywhere in the given expression,
5964/// or subexpressions.
5965static bool isSymbolUsedInExpression(const MCSymbol *Sym, const MCExpr *Value) {
5966 switch (Value->getKind()) {
5967 case MCExpr::Binary: {
5968 const MCBinaryExpr *BE = static_cast<const MCBinaryExpr *>(Value);
5969 return isSymbolUsedInExpression(Sym, BE->getLHS()) ||
5970 isSymbolUsedInExpression(Sym, BE->getRHS());
5971 }
5972 case MCExpr::Target:
5973 case MCExpr::Constant:
5974 return false;
5975 case MCExpr::SymbolRef: {
5976 const MCSymbol &S =
5977 static_cast<const MCSymbolRefExpr *>(Value)->getSymbol();
5978 if (S.isVariable())
5979 return isSymbolUsedInExpression(Sym, S.getVariableValue());
5980 return &S == Sym;
5981 }
5982 case MCExpr::Unary:
5983 return isSymbolUsedInExpression(
5984 Sym, static_cast<const MCUnaryExpr *>(Value)->getSubExpr());
5985 }
5986
5987 llvm_unreachable("Unknown expr kind!");
5988}
5989
5990bool parseAssignmentExpression(StringRef Name, bool allow_redef,
5991 MCAsmParser &Parser, MCSymbol *&Sym,
5992 const MCExpr *&Value) {
5993
5994 // FIXME: Use better location, we should use proper tokens.
5995 SMLoc EqualLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
5996 if (Parser.parseExpression(Value))
5997 return Parser.TokError("missing expression");
5998
5999 // Note: we don't count b as used in "a = b". This is to allow
6000 // a = b
6001 // b = c
6002
6003 if (Parser.parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
6004 return true;
6005
6006 // Validate that the LHS is allowed to be a variable (either it has not been
6007 // used as a symbol, or it is an absolute symbol).
6008 Sym = Parser.getContext().lookupSymbol(Name);
6009 if (Sym) {
6010 // Diagnose assignment to a label.
6011 //
6012 // FIXME: Diagnostics. Note the location of the definition as a label.
6013 // FIXME: Diagnose assignment to protected identifier (e.g., register name).
6014 if (isSymbolUsedInExpression(Sym, Value))
6015 return Parser.Error(EqualLoc, "Recursive use of '" + Name + "'");
6016 else if (Sym->isUndefined(/*SetUsed*/ false) && !Sym->isUsed() &&
6017 !Sym->isVariable())
6018 ; // Allow redefinitions of undefined symbols only used in directives.
6019 else if (Sym->isVariable() && !Sym->isUsed() && allow_redef)
6020 ; // Allow redefinitions of variables that haven't yet been used.
6021 else if (!Sym->isUndefined() && (!Sym->isVariable() || !allow_redef))
6022 return Parser.Error(EqualLoc, "redefinition of '" + Name + "'");
6023 else if (!Sym->isVariable())
6024 return Parser.Error(EqualLoc, "invalid assignment to '" + Name + "'");
6025 else if (!isa<MCConstantExpr>(Sym->getVariableValue()))
6026 return Parser.Error(EqualLoc,
6027 "invalid reassignment of non-absolute variable '" +
6028 Name + "'");
6029 } else if (Name == ".") {
6030 Parser.getStreamer().emitValueToOffset(Value, 0, EqualLoc);
6031 return false;
6032 } else
6033 Sym = Parser.getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Name);
6034
6035 Sym->setRedefinable(allow_redef);
6036
6037 return false;
6038}
